{"name":"Mark of Scribing","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast one of the following spells:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Mark]{arcane mark}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Message]{message}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{speak language}</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The heir has 10 dedicated Power Points that recharge normally. She automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} for 2 additional Power Points. She&nbsp;may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Sivis]{Mark of Scribing} doesn't grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the heir also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or Power Points can be used with the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Sivis]{Mark of Scribing} (and vice-versa).</p>\n<p>Additionally, pick any one of the following skills: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Language]{Language}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, and add +1 to the total whenever they are used.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Gnome"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172637,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"0WhxodGz26nAylFn","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Wizard)","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/orb-hands-humanoid-yellow.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_2i5x75676ju","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Wizard)]{Arcane Background (Wizard)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171715,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"0cILksGLzuFqCSxP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Improved Extraction","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.4s9P4ksJQuJFwcTE"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Up to three foes' (player's choice) don't get attacks when your warrior @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{moves out of melee} with them</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Extraction"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172324,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"0qdV8t8mH7mAKoFK","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Brawny","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[{"_id":"xD9SM5eqeRZvcjF6","changes":[{"key":"system.stats.size","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null},{"key":"system.attributes.strength.encumbranceSteps","mode":2,"value":"2","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","label":"Brawny","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.LYYfJsMEFfJVmelT"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your bruiser is very large or very fit. Her @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} increases by +1 (and therefore @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness} by 1) and she treats her @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Strength} as one die type higher when determining <strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Gear Notes]{Encumbrance}</strong><strong> </strong>and <strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Minimum Strength]{Minimum Strength} </strong>to use armor, weapons, and equipment without a penalty.</p>\n<p>Brawny can't increase a character's Size above +3.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Vigor d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172021,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"11VfvMXKuEwkzdtT","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Danger Sense","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ueibkknhw27","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.3NXC55lkdPQyW82P"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your hero can sense when something bad is about to happen. When rolling for <strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Surprise]{Surprise}</strong>, he adds +2 to his @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll to act in the first round. With a raise, he starts the encounter on @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hold]{Hold}.</p>\n<p>In other situations not covered by the Surprise rules (a sniper shot, pit trap, poisoned drink, etc.), Danger Sense gives him a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll at &minus;2 (or +2 if a Notice roll is usually allowed) to detect the hazard and take appropriate action. If this was an attack and the hero makes his Notice roll, the foe doesn't get @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.OPSttc2CAS2LC1ju.JournalEntryPage.l1rEt2RnvcIiEGtQ]{The Drop} against him.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Weird Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173324,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"13amXHKt4Rerp6Cf","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mount","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.uZSxRkVLgxzgUxxR"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero has a mount that is hardier and more clever than most and utterly loyal to its master (even if it&rsquo;s cantankerous or otherwise disagreeable).</p>\n<p>Normal Size heroes may have a riding horse, war horse, or elven horse (with the DM's permission). Smaller heroes may also choose a boar, large cat, dire wolf, or wolf. Other mounts may be available as makes sense for the character and the setting. Whatever the beast, its @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} is one die type higher than normal and it&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.UA76PiL4485vout2]{Resilient}.</p>\n<p>For each of your character&rsquo;s current @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Ranks}, and each time he gains a new @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Rank} thereafter, the mount gains one of the following effects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Increase a @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Trait} one die type, no more than once per Trait.</li>\n<li>Gain an Edge or Monstrous ability that makes sense for its species (DM's call). It must meet the Requirements as usual.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Death:</strong> If the mount perishes, another takes its place eventually, perhaps after a narrative encounter or visit to a place where such creatures can be tamed or purchased.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">GREAT MOUNT:</span> At Heroic @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Rank} you may choose to keep your mount and @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Advance} it normally, or dismiss it for a &ldquo;Great Mount.&rdquo; (Or simply take a Great Mount if you didn&rsquo;t have this Edge previously.) <br />Normal Size heroes may choose a bear, dinosaur (giant herbivore or pterosaur), elephant, giant animal (bird, centipede, scorpion, toad), griffin, hippogriff, pegasus, sabre-toothed tiger, unicorn, or wyvern. Small heroes may also choose a dinosaur (velociraptor), giant animal (ant, crab, lizard), lion, or peryton. <br />A Great Mounts&rsquo; @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} is one die type higher than normal, it&rsquo;s Very Resilient, and it gains one @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Advance} for each of its master&rsquo;s @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Ranks} as described above.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">LEGENDARY MOUNT:</span> At Legendary @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Rank} you may choose to keep your mount and @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Advance} it normally, or dismiss it for a &ldquo;Legendary Mount.&rdquo; (Or simply take a Legendary Mount if you didn&rsquo;t have this Edge previously.) <br />Normal Size heroes may choose to ride dinosaur (tyrannosaurus rex), a dragon (young, the player chooses the type of dragon and breath weapon), drake, mammoth, roc, or tree folk (young). Smaller heroes may ride a dragon (young).<br />A Legendary Mounts&rsquo; @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} is one die type higher than normal, it&rsquo;s a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.IZ9YJamVRZdr4VVU]{Wild Card}, and it gains one @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Advance} for each of its master&rsquo;s @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Ranks} as described above.</li>\n</ul>\n<aside class=\"sidebar\">\n<p>Normal mounts may be purchased or acquired through play, but aren&rsquo;t loyal to their master and aren&rsquo;t replaced and don&rsquo;t advance like those taken with the Mount Edge.</p>\n<p>How these special animals enter the game should be given some thought and a bit of narrative. Such a rare beast might be a reward for some service, the bounty of a grateful deity, conquered in battle, or saved from some dire fate.</p>\n<p>The Dungeon Master and player should take work together to describe how the beast was encountered and tamed. It should also be named and given its own personality and minor character traits that make it stand out from others of its kind.</p>\n</aside>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Riding d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173066,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"1D2FRty40tr8dMAZ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/orb-hands-humanoid-yellow.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_2i5x75676ju","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)]{Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171616,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Fame","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.ctY41MWqmubD1ATI"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your character is a minor celebrity of some sort. She might be a popular bard known in a particular fiefdom, a minor rock star, or a beloved B-movie actor.</span></p>\n<p>She makes double the normal fee when performing for pay (see </span><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}</span></strong>). She can also use her celebrity to add +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls if a target is friendly and knows who she is (a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} roll modified by how likely the individual is to know the celebrity).<br /></span></p>\n<p>The downside of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fame]{Fame} is that the individual is often recognized, others frequently want something from her, she may be followed by fans or admirers, or she may not be able to shirk obligations, performances, or other duties without causing trouble for herself.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172053,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"1KtyM3zUY9D6Tdjh","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"House Scion","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This individual was born into the privilege of a dragonmarked house or came into it later in life. She may or may not have money (the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rich]{Rich} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Filthy Rich]{Filthy Rich} Edge), but she still walks in the elite circles of the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Dragonmarks]{dragonmarked houses}.</p>\n<p>This character will likely be able to take on the name of their house for a last name, denoting being a scion of the house.</p>\n<p>House scions add +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} when @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} with other house members and in any other circumstances where being a member of a dragonmarked house would impact such rolls. They also add +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls made to know the information about what is going on within their house, recognize family names or members of their house, or recall gossip concerning others within their house.</p>\n<p>From time to time you also can call on the contacts within your family to gain important information that might be known to them. Or perhaps you can call in a favor to acquire the loan of equipment, access to important documents, contact with influential acquaintances, or even professional services. The DM has final say in if a favor can be called in and what can be provided by it.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Dragonmarked Race"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172124,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"1ToF3AzAS8lQ7sud","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"_id":"1W5SmuzOuGIcSlyu","name":"Heroic Aura","type":"edge","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/bust-carved-stone.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kouunmqxeo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Glory Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>Times may be taken: </strong>4</p>\n<p>True heroes have destinies beyond those of lesser men. As a hero becomes more famous, so his fate becomes more important. Lesser foes no longer present the danger they once did, and only the mightiest enemies give the hero pause.</p>\n<p>When not wearing armor (he may use a shield), he gains +1 @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness} each time he takes this benefit. While wearing armor, no benefit is gained. Encumbrance plays no part in this benefit&mdash;the modifier is gained even if the hero is heavily weighed down with other gear.</p>\n<p>In game terms, taking this benefit once grants the protection equivalent of cloth armor, but it cannot be reduced by @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} weapons, protects against area effect attacks, and has zero encumbrance. With a second benefit, the hero as well protected as wearing light armor, three times medium armor, a fourth time heavy armor.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Glory Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"40+ Glory"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172686,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Scholar","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Learned professors, devoted students, and amateur enthusiasts spend great amounts of time and energy studying particular subjects. They become experts in these fields, and rarely fail to answer questions in their particular area of expertise.</p>\n<p>Pick any of the following skills: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Science]{Science}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Religion]{Religion}. +1 can be added to any two skills <em>or</em> +2 can be added to any one skill.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be taken more than once if applied to different skills.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173083,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"1txg3o2lEljrQIXg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Home Ground","type":"edge","img":"icons/sundries/flags/banner-symbol-axe-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fsvlz5d67ma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.C6LLdePT8MWJFhhd"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>There are few things more dangerous than a druid in her home forest, a wizard in his lair, or a necromancer in the ruined city his undead horde have built for him. Working with the Dungeon Master, designate one area as your hero&rsquo;s &ldquo;home.&rdquo; This might be an entire forest, bay, coastline, or lake and its surroundings for a druid, a church and the small town it serves for a cleric, a tower and its environs for a wizard or elementalist, or a keep full of contraptions and chemicals for an alchemist or tinkerer.</p>\n<p>Once per encounter, while within this area, the character may spend a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.RkejkA1MLhB8IeFe]{Benny} to recover all her Power Points. The mage also has a sense of her home, no matter how distant she may be. She may concentrate for ten minutes (one minute if on her Home Ground) to ask three questions about the current, observable state of her homeland, revealed through scrying, visions, or other eldritch sense.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Legendary Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary, Spirit d8+, Arcane Background (Any)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172821,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"24LGbmlzZLy3m2GK","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mark of Passage","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast one of the following spells:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Leaping]{leaping}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{speed}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Animal]{summon animal}</em> (mount only)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>All powers (except <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{summon beast}</em>) have a range of touch only, but the heir gains no benefit from the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The heir has 10 dedicated Power Points that recharge normally. He automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} for 2 additional Power Points.&nbsp;He may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Orien]{Mark of Passage} doesn't grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the heir also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or Power Points can be used with the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Orien]{Mark of Passage} (and vice-versa).</p>\n<p>Additionally, pick any one of the following skills: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Riding]{Riding}, and add +1 to the total whenever they are used.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Human"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172634,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"2CHzraZd3EIEL272","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
