{"_id":"2qMBCh8Yer8icpE7","name":"Work the Crowd","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tbo7kidroy","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.tydCtcB76NXWLlSH"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your hero's words don't just inspire those they're directed at&mdash;they often inspire others as well. Once per turn, you can use Work the Crowd to roll two additional skill dice when @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Supporting} with @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}. The additional dice Support up to three allies who can see or hear your hero, and applies to their next action, whatever it may be.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Social Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Work the Room"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173204,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Improved Nerves of Steel","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[{"_id":"bj2aGVtr5w9yWqK8","changes":[{"key":"system.wounds.ignored","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Improved Nerves of Steel","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.2C7ArLMnoXCBjHiB"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero ignores two points of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Nerves of Steel"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172353,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"3AQmbSyTUi3rcBzB","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Ferocious Summoning","type":"edge","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/deer-movement-leap-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A summoner with this Edge has learned to conjure fiercer, more experienced beasts with the <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.UIabn5crJiOlr5Hk]{summon monster}</em>&nbsp;power. He may grant them any one Combat Edge of <em>his </em>Rank or lower.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Summoner), summon monster"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171807,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"3AfBOgMceUUG6JWh","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mr Fix It","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.KyGQq6uYSc9UNzJo"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The mechanic adds +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} rolls. With a raise, he halves the time normally required to fix something. This means if a particular Repair job says a raise repairs it in half the time, a Mr Fix It can finish the job in one quarter the time with a raise.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Repair d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173069,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"3KfVDCgrHplTnwYv","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Martial Warrior","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.alxaZpc27RkDsI3l"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The fighter has trained in martial arts. Her fists and feet are weapons (see <strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}</strong> so she's always considered armed. She adds +2 when striking with them and causes @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Strength}+d6 damage. If she already has a Strength damage die from the <strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Special Ability (Claws)]{Claws}</strong> racial ability or the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brawler]{Brawler} Edge, increase the damage a die type.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist} does <em>not</em> add to damage from other Natural Weapons such as fangs or horns.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Martial Artist"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172420,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"3cumTS46ZM6XhSxG","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"_id":"3rubjnx3YSnvrFKW","name":"Retort","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tbo7kidroy","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Ln73rU0W1nXvlmWC"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This verbal duelist can turn the slings and arrows of social combat right back at the unwitting fools who hurled them.</span></p>\n<p>If a character with Retort gets a raise when resisting an @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test}, the </span>foe </span>is @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.OPSttc2CAS2LC1ju.JournalEntryPage.vsS5QN7dPw9CFsBo]{Distracted}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Social Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Intimidation d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173185,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Wrestler","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero is trained in holds, locks, and takedowns. She may roll @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} instead of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} when @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Grappling]{Grappling}. She may also roll @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Strength}+d4 when @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Grappling]{Crushing}. If she already has a damage die from @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Natural Weapons]{Claws}, the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brawler]{Brawler} Edges, etc., increase the damage die by one type instead.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility or Strength d6+, Fighting d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172533,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"41Y1iekwH9T0Pegq","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Warlock/Witch)","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/orb-hands-humanoid-yellow.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.AiuViCNsPg67wXyk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2i5x75676ju","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Warlock/Witch)]{Arcane Background (Warlock/Witch)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171703,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"46MCDysP3aab0lDy","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Greater Mark of Warding","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast the additional following power:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{arcane protection}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>All Powers have the range of touch only, but the heir gains no benefit from the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>He may now also access any Epic Power modifiers to any powers offered by his dragonmark.</p>\n<p>Additionally the dragonmarked heir gains 5 more Power Points for his dragonmarked powers.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Mark of Warding"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172603,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"4FZhJACmSAxih86n","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Brute","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Uo6iHEZgrx5L4Zqw"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Brutes focus on core strength and fitness over coordination and flexibility. They treat @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} as linked to @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Strength} instead of @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Agility} for purposes of @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Advancement}. The character may also resist Athletics @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Tests} with Strength if she chooses. </span></p>\n<p>Finally, Brutes increase the </span>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Short Range} of any thrown item by +1. Double that for the adjusted Medium Range, and double again for Long Range. If a thrown item's Range is 3/6/12, for example, a Brute's Range is 4/8/16.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Vigor d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172030,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"4ddDchXqgnUFIqMZ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Arcane Barding","type":"edge","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/deer-movement-leap-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The caster&rsquo;s animals appear swathed in eldritch barding forged from magical energies. This increases their Toughness by +2 and cannot be <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.N0LX7ogCmpSL81t7]{dispelled}</em>.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Summoner), summon animal"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171738,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"4wAp0281v8OxfIpi","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Famous","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.vzVxOjBsqtaxvCvo"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your hero is truly famous. She's wellknown in a large circle such as a country, a large industry, or a popular medium (film or television, the music industry). She makes 5 &times; the normal fee when performing and adds +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls when influencing friendly individuals who know who she is.</span></p>\n<p>The price is higher for the truly @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Famous]{Famous}, too, with more demands on her time, obligations, rivals, scandals, and an inability to operate in crowds without being recognized.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fame"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172064,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"512PC1CCMQmMMKx0","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Undead Familiar","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/death/hand-dirt-undead-zombie.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The necromancer gains an undead animal companion that serves as his familiar. This works exactly as the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.iNjX3XpoWt1uXGjf]{Familiar} Edge except the creature gains the Undead ability:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.yh2PPJnWWWpxDgZt]{Undead}:</strong> +2 Toughness; +2 to recover from being Shaken; no additional damage from @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.OPSttc2CAS2LC1ju.JournalEntryPage.FtSdZK9mueD0Pkz0]{Called Shots}; ignores 1 point of Wound penalties; doesn&rsquo;t breathe; immune to disease and poison.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Necromancer)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171924,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"5CvLQdX4UUPfR6de","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Inspire Heroics","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/music-singing-voice-blue.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Bards inspire their comrades with epic tales of valor and bravery. Once during any combat encounter (DM&rsquo;s call), the bard can spend a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.RkejkA1MLhB8IeFe]{Benny}&nbsp;to gain five Inspiration tokens. This is a limited free action.</p>\n<p>For the remainder of the encounter, the bard may give these tokens to anyone within a Range of @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} except himself. This may be done at any time (as long as the bard is conscious). The recipient must use the token immediately&mdash;it cannot be saved.</p>\n<p>Each Inspiration token allows a character to reroll a Trait or damage roll. A Trait or damage roll may only benefit from a single Inspiration Token, even if there are multiple bards present. Further rerolls require spending a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.RkejkA1MLhB8IeFe]{Benny} or a special ability.</p>\n<p>Inspiration tokens aren&rsquo;t @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.RkejkA1MLhB8IeFe]{Bennies}, don&rsquo;t trigger Edges that use @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.RkejkA1MLhB8IeFe]{Bennies} (such as @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.cQBs3kKA3cUO13Xe]{Elan}), and can&rsquo;t be used as such in any other way such as drawing new @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.b0BBoKY0d5GZgOVk]{Action Cards} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.CJOnuNywSJDpO7hK]{Soaking Wounds}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Bard), Performance d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171838,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"5IKhreE4fNJurFe6","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"_id":"5QNOOXJNoXxxY7ow","name":"Menacing","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tbo7kidroy","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.WRpK5JTq57sLcfOq"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Being a brutish lout isn't always a drawback if you know how to use it. Menacing allows a character to put her bad looks or worse attitude to good use. The goon adds +2 to her @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} rolls.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Social Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, any one of Bloodthirsty, Grim, Mean, Ruthless, or Ugly"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173168,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Blood Magic","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Z5thwi3zWWr2HXC1"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The character channels his arcane power through an evil or malevolent source, or has learned to draw power through the pain and misery of others.</p>\n<p>Every time the mage causes a Wound to a conscious, sapient being of some sort (and the Wound isn&rsquo;t Soaked), he recovers a d6 Power Points. The caster must cause the damage directly, using his powers, bare hands, weapons, and so on. He gains no benefit from indirect harm such as that caused by a <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.JD9spUOc5xOQLuqa]{puppeted}</em> foe, ally, zombie, pet, or minion.</p>\n<p>Those suspected of practicing such tainted magic are often hunted by local authorities. Sometimes there are entire orders dedicated to their eradication. When caught, the sentence is almost always slow, painful, and fatal.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Any), an evil disposition"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172885,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"5ShMWAkfWMtaIlym","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Great Summoning","type":"edge","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/deer-movement-leap-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The mage can conjure beasts most others can&rsquo;t, including a barghest for 5 points, a mammoth for 7 points, a frost mammoth for 8 points, a tyrannosaurus rex for 8 points, or a drake for 9 points.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Arcane Background (Summoner), summon animal, summon monster"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171818,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"5YD4japjyWBnxvM1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Fleet-Footed","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[{"_id":"mFoHbGDlICVd3Daw","changes":[{"key":"system.stats.speed.runningDie","mode":2,"value":"2","priority":null},{"key":"system.stats.speed.value","mode":2,"value":"2","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","label":"Fleet-Footed","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.PTPwOeAxgwnjCiIv"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero's @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#movement]{Pace} is increased by +2 and his @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#movement]{running die} increases one step (from d6 to d8, for example)</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172105,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"6GtdnvpRqsbuftuy","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mystic Powers (Ranger)","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Qt3tD20Pgq0u9P9k"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In worlds where magic is relatively common, disciplined adventurers may learn a few simple powers to help them in their quests. Choose one of the packages below. The character has 10 dedicated Power Points that recharge normally. As a limited free action, the hero automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a raise for an additional 2 Power Points. She may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).</p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges that require an Arcane Background, but she may take the Power Points or Soul Drain Edge. If the hero also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges or abilities can be used with Mystic Powers and viceversa.</p>\n<p>Abilities noted as &ldquo;Self Only&rdquo; do not get any additional benefit from that Limitation.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.i78Y7jme40GZiRcI]{Beast Friend}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Aii4dhYLbc4Xf8mf]{Boost Trait}</em> (<em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.SzVzIV8ZxqKg3Oe3]{Athletics}</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.MIvf1ckXhEyM27uv]{Fighting}</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.L2Z2vXl1K5GMZCXm]{Shooting}</em>, or<em> @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.QwL1xSthAdQEK60D]{Survival}</em>&nbsp;only)</li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.ful8IniWqVVlMrP9]{Entangle}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.mwJrHdTGvCLVbrhu]{Farsight}</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>All but <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.i78Y7jme40GZiRcI]{beast friend}</em> and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.ful8IniWqVVlMrP9]{entangle}</em> have the Self Limitation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Survival d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172963,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"6Vdq6kSdCW4YZYC6","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
