{"_id":"BXMHzJemKM92rHzb","name":"Strong Willed","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tbo7kidroy","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.LXKTnJkZTAKTl9hs"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Self-confidence is powerful armor against those who attempt to attack this individual's will. He adds +2 to his total when resisting @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Tests} with @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} or @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Spirit}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Social Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173200,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mark of Making","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast the following powers:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{conjure item}</em> (no Create Food and Water.)</li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect/conceal arcana}</em> (no alignment sense)</li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{repair}</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{Detect/Conceal Arcana}</em> has a range of touch only, but the heir gains no benefit from the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The heir has 10 dedicated Power Points that recharge normally. He automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} for 2 additional Power Points. He may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Cannith]{Mark of Making} doesn't grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the heir also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or Power Points can be used with the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Cannith]{Mark of Making} (and vice-versa).</p>\n<p>Additionally,&nbsp;Pick any one of the following skills: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Science]{Science}, and add +1 to the total whenever they are used.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Human"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172631,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"Bg9uVNfJIVwo5yln","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Master of Illusion","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-slit-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The caster&rsquo;s illusions have the Mobility and Sound Power Modifiers at no additional Power Point cost.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Illusionist), Spellcasting d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171866,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"BuwtKaH4XZ7SJHXe","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Command","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u9f0tp9vn2","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.dyvT3rgFdOvNN2vZ"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Command is the basic ability to give clear instructions and support to allies in the thick of battle. Extras in </span>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Command Range} add +1 to their @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Spirit} rolls when attempting to recover from being @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} and +1 to @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Vigor} rolls when attempting to recover from being @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.OPSttc2CAS2LC1ju.JournalEntryPage.37hOhcNkT98KKtAv]{Stunned}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Leadership Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172733,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"CMyAkKs90r3Z8c2d","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Finely Tuned","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The artificer has studied under the best masters in his field and has fine tuned his creations to maximum efficiency.</p>\n<p>When creating an <strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Devices]{Arcane Device}</strong>, each raise an artificer gets on his activation roll reduces the cost of the power by 1 Power Point, to a minimum of 1. The Arcane Device must have the full points available to use the power in the first place before rolling. You only need to take this Edge once, not for each Arcane Device.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Craft Arcane Device, Repair d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Slipstream"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172916,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"CQV9kwTWZhf4bua3","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Craft Arcane Device","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Those who tangle with supernatural forces sometimes find ways to imbue powers into items. They may turn an ordinary blade into a magic sword, grant powerful potions to their friends, or even bless holy relics with divine grace.</p>\n<p>The hero can create <strong> @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.6 Arcane Devices]{arcane devices}</strong> and give them to their allies. Where possible, the device reflects the forger's background. A bard's Arcane Devices are works of art, such as a singing sword, a magical instrument, an epic poem, etc.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any but Psion), Arcana or Repair d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172897,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"CahocAsJkE9e2uAa","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Sweep","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{limited action}, Sweep allows a character to make a single @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack with a two-handed weapon and apply it against all targets in his @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reach]{Reach} at a &minus;2 penalty (friends and foes alike). Resolve damage separately for each enemy that's hit.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Some creatures have the Sweep Edge even though they don't have two-handed weapons. In their case their size, lanky limbs, or other advantages allow them to make Sweep attacks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Fighting d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172505,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"CdIeXlr0LcFJLIgr","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Favored Enemy","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.WJWhWMT8RhtaJjqt"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your hero has fought a particular type of enemy for many years. She knows how best to attack and defend against them, and where their weak spots are.</p>\n<p>Choose a type of enemy native to your character&rsquo;s homeland or backstory, such as undead, fey, demons, constructs, giants, animals, or a particular ancestry such as elves or dwarves.</p>\n<p>Your hero doesn&rsquo;t trust or like members of that race (&ndash;2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.TY6Vt7W3PY07fKSz]{Persuasion} rolls when interacting with them), but knows how to fight them. She gets one free reroll when failing to track (@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.QwL1xSthAdQEK60D]{Survival}) or attack (@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.SzVzIV8ZxqKg3Oe3]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.MIvf1ckXhEyM27uv]{Fighting}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.L2Z2vXl1K5GMZCXm]{Shooting}) that type of being.</p>\n<p>You may take this Edge more than once to reflect experience with multiple types of foes.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172073,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"Cl0eNxhVcqWJHoDU","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mystic Powers (Rogue)","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Qt3tD20Pgq0u9P9k"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In worlds where magic is relatively common, disciplined adventurers may learn a few simple powers to help them in their quests. Choose one of the packages below. The character has 10 dedicated Power Points that recharge normally. As a limited free action, the hero automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a raise for an additional 2 Power Points. She may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).</p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges that require an Arcane Background, but she may take the Power Points or Soul Drain Edge. If the hero also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges or abilities can be used with Mystic Powers and viceversa.</p>\n<p>Abilities noted as &ldquo;Self Only&rdquo; do not get any additional benefit from that Limitation.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Aii4dhYLbc4Xf8mf]{Boost Trait}</em> (<em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.SzVzIV8ZxqKg3Oe3]{Athletics}</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.RETQQlxjJduSt01S]{Deception}</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.lCPTPB1Y1oD2bag0]{Stealth}</em>, or <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.WT0ARsSIm2WDQbW3]{Thievery}</em>&nbsp;only)</li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.mKUgFQiQwiGSSFP9]{Darksight}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.4Y6vWKSXhpV6Am3H]{Lock/Unlock}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.gGgeoMVnqCjbE9cy]{Wall Walker}</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>All have the Self Limitation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Thievery d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172965,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"CoizjuCDEVNBKazo","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Legendary Storyteller","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The party gains +1d8 @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Glory and Infamy]{Glory} for each raise after the first when using the Variable Glory Awards.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Master Storyteller"},"grants":[],"source":"Hellfrost"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173049,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"DHWi8ppemyziybwh","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Siege Breaker","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_u9f0tp9vn2","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}. The hero has a good knowledge of siege warfare and can spot weaknesses in enemy fortifications.</p>\n<p>When he leads the army, the character reduces the Siege Bonus of any fortification his men are attacking by 1 (to a minimum of zero).</p>\n<p>If he makes a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} roll at the start of a siege, he can increase the Siege Bonus penalty by an additional &minus;1 for success and &minus;2 with a raise by studying and exploiting specific weaknesses.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Leadership Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Command, Battle d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Hellfrost"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172788,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"DXsxiDas34FcquvZ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Fey Blood","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.WJWhWMT8RhtaJjqt"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Elves, half-elves, and certain fey are often resistant to hostile magic. Those with some amount of it in their blood get a free reroll when resisting enemy powers and spelllike effects.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172088,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"DvsnkbZfJnpIgQmV","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Cleric)","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/orb-hands-humanoid-yellow.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_2i5x75676ju","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Cleric)]{Arcane Background (Cleric)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171637,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"E6yOW6PfzFWgHuPD","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"_id":"EMdniU77ZTlMW3xj","name":"Sidekick","type":"edge","img":"icons/sundries/flags/banner-symbol-axe-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_fsvlz5d67ma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.8RxZs4z3UMw9dbSi"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A character who triumphs over evil time and time again becomes an inspiration to others. Eventually, one of these young crusaders may attempt to join the hero in his epic quests.</p>\n<p>The hero gains a @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Novice Rank} sidekick. The sidekick is a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}, starts each session with two @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.NUjlHH5PBpH1dlzH#bennies]{Bennies}, may @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Advance}, and has abilities that complement his mentor. The player character controls his sidekick just like any other ally, though he may occasionally cause trouble by getting captured, running into danger when he's not supposed to, and so on. The player should be prepared for his Edge to occasionally become a Hindrance!</p>\n<p>If the sidekick dies, he isn't replaced unless the hero chooses this Edge again. Fortunately, heroes may always spend Bennies for their sidekicks as if she had the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Common Bond]{Common Bond} Edge. Sidekicks must actually take that Edge to do the same for their mentors.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Legendary Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172837,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Greater Mark of Hospitality","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast the additional following power:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Plane Shift]{plane shift}</em> (Extra-dimensional space only)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Plane Shift]{Plane shift}</em>&nbsp;has the range of touch only, but the heir gains no benefit from the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>She may now also access any Epic Power modifiers to any powers offered by her dragonmark.</p>\n<p>Additionally the dragonmarked heir gains 5 more Power Points for her dragonmarked powers.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Mark of Hospitality"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172573,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ENwhD6b0YibTC6LQ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Dodge","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.9jMwSbUFO7eLQpHN"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero can anticipate attacks or move erratically under fire. Unless the victim of a surprise attack and taken completely unaware, Dodge subtracts 2 from all @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Attacks]{ranged attacks} made against the character. Dodge does </span>not </span>stack with actual @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, however</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172250,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"EPePT5vbmNyAwwJ4","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Takedown Move","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>When the hero successfully @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Push]{Pushes} an opponent, the opponent must make an @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll at &ndash;2 (&ndash;4 if the hero got a raise) or be knocked @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Prone]{prone}.</p>\n<p>The wrestler can also chose not to push the opponent 1\" away, but just @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Prone]{prone}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Wrestler"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172517,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ERt017TFzxNyK8Wy","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Professional","type":"edge","img":"icons/sundries/flags/banner-symbol-axe-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fsvlz5d67ma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.LiXbGtoJY8x1fc0c"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The character is an expert at a particular skill or attribute (his choice). This increases the @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Trait} and its limit one step (a d12+1 becomes a d12+2, for example). This Edge may be selected once per Trait.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Legendary Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, maximum die type possible in affected Trait"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172835,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"EVb2HOGiEkrVZOQM","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Drop!","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_u9f0tp9vn2","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Once per round when a ranged weapon targets an ally within the hero's command radius, the character may order him to drop to the ground. This allows the intended target to fall @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Prone]{prone} out of turn, even if he has acted already, gaining the benefits of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{Medium Cover}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Leadership Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Notice d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172751,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"Eb0Y4OKsEOemhVov","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Troubadour","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[{"_id":"lWVjTffzXQrDqt1r","changes":[{"key":"@Skill{Common Knowledge}[system.die.modifier]","mode":2,"value":"2","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","label":"Troubadour","transfer":true,"flags":{"swade":{"expiration":null,"loseTurnOnHold":false}},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Troubadours travel the world, learning culture, etiquette, history, and above all, legends.</p>\n<p>They add +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls and may use @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} in place of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} for Leadership @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.MAcvE2WNI1eEy4R8]{Edges} or @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.MAcvE2WNI1eEy4R8]{Edges} that require @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Common Knowledge d6+, Performance d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173116,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"EfUisqq6GvSsPhxj","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"The Evil Eye","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/perception/hand-eye-fire-blue.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.olo05rxG7sk33Bpt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Powerful witches and warlocks are known for their baleful stares. Locals call this the &ldquo;evil eye,&rdquo; even if the mage is actually pure of heart.</p>\n<p>Once per encounter, a witch may target an intelligent being within 6&rdquo; (12 yards). For the rest of that encounter, the target must make a Spirit roll at &ndash;2 to spend a Benny.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Warlock/Witch)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171905,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"EguggR6EISrIDTKG","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Greater Mark of Handling","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast the additional following power:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{speak language} (beasts only)</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{Speak language}</em> has the range of touch only, but the heir gains no benefit from the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>He may now also access any Epic Power modifiers to any powers offered by his dragonmark.</p>\n<p>Additionally the dragonmarked heir gains 5 more Power Points for his dragonmarked powers.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Mark of Handling"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172564,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"EiiGkiMIDwmDhmOK","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Aristocrat","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This individual was born into privilege or came into it later in life. She may or may not have money (the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rich]{Rich} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Filthy Rich]{Filthy Rich} Edge), but she still walks in the elite social circles of the setting.</p>\n<p>This character will likely be able to place ir' before their last name to denote being a member of the nobility.</p>\n<p>Aristocrats add +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} when @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} with the local elite, captains of industry, nobles, or other aristocrats. They also add +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls made to know the etiquette of the upper class, recognize family trees or heraldry, or recall gossip concerning others of their station.</p>\n<p>Typically, a character with this edge has the lowest noble title (his father being one or two steps higher up the social ladder). The character also rules a small manor, small village, or hamlet. Only with the DM's permission may the character begin at a higher social status.</p>\n<p>Further social promotions require family members to move aside (or die) to allow the character to assume a new title, and this should be worked into the campaign.</p>\n<h2>Other Form of \"Nobility\"</h2>\n<p>While the Noble Edge typically covers those born to high station, this is not a firm dictate. The Edge can also be used to represent other character types. A player who wants to use the Noble Edge in an atypical way should always consult with his DM first.</p>\n<p>For instance, a cleric with the Edge may be the head of a small temple. A hero may also be a guildmaster. Normally this should be a legitimate guild, but with the DM's permission, the hero may run a small thieves' guild. A hero may be a guildmaster for a craft guild or perhaps run a way station for one of the dragonmarked houses. The hero must handle labor disputes, raids by the thieves' guild, and so on.</p>\n<p>Although a merchant can be represented by the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rich]{Rich} Edge, one taking the Aristocract Edge might be a well-known merchant or have a sizable business. In return for the +2 @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} bonus, he also has the hassle of balancing the books, negotiating contracts, fighting off competitors, and such like.</p>\n<p>Characters using Artistocract in an alternate way do not gain the titles listed elsewhere. DMs and players should work together to create suitable honorifics.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"},"grants":[],"source":"748410"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171973,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"EodaX1WBgR36f4bq","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Poisoner","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.uZSxRkVLgxzgUxxR"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The character is an expert with poisons. She creates poisons in half the time. In addition, her contact poisons last 12 hours rather than four.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Healing, Science, or Survival d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173072,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"Eot17g8ohHBNfe0T","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mark of Detection","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast the following powers:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em> (<em>@UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Agility}, @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}</em>, and any \"knowledge\" based skill only)</li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana}</em> (no Identify)</li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Locate]{locate}</em> (poisons and traps only)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait}</em> has the range of touch only, but the heir gains no benefit from the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The heir has 10 dedicated Power Points that recharge normally. He automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} for 2 additional Power Points. He may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Medani]{Mark of Detection} doesn't grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the heir also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or Power Points can be used with the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Medani]{Mark of Detection} (and vice-versa).</p>\n<p>Additionally pick any one of the following skills: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}, and add +1 to the total whenever they are used.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Half-elf"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172606,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"EwsX2CypcFVFDGLP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mystic Powers (Monk)","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Qt3tD20Pgq0u9P9k"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In worlds where magic is relatively common, disciplined adventurers may learn a few simple powers to help them in their quests. Choose one of the packages below. The character has 10 dedicated Power Points that recharge normally. As a limited free action, the hero automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a raise for an additional 2 Power Points. She may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).</p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges that require an Arcane Background, but she may take the Power Points or Soul Drain Edge. If the hero also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges or abilities can be used with Mystic Powers and viceversa.</p>\n<p>Abilities noted as &ldquo;Self Only&rdquo; do not get any additional benefit from that Limitation.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Aii4dhYLbc4Xf8mf]{Boost Trait}</em> (<em>Agility</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.SzVzIV8ZxqKg3Oe3]{Athletics}</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.MIvf1ckXhEyM27uv]{Fighting}</em>, <em>Spirit</em>, or <em>Vigor</em> only)</li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sb5DePEKWohVXVmg]{Deflection}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.hUoU4cSN6b5UmO4f]{Smite}</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>All have the Self Limitation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Athletics d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172951,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"F1JFveGV6FtCvK3n","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Storm Chaser","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ueibkknhw27","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>When the weather is at its worst the character is at his best, seeming to read the storm like he would a book. Such characters are respected for their skill but feared for their love of a good storm.</p>\n<p>The character receives +1 to all @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} rolls made during a storm, using his knowledge of his vessel and how best to mitigate the damage from the stormy winds.</p>\n<p>In addition, the character may draw two cards during a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Storms at Sea]{storm} and keep the best card, as long as he is the Captain. If the character has the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wind Sense]{Wind Sense} Edge as well he draws three cards.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Weird Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Boating or Piloting d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"50 Fathoms"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173346,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"F9HRCThJ1gv1OuAl","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Luck","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[{"_id":"OWnLq0po631TdzRm","changes":[{"key":"system.bennies.max","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","label":"Luck","transfer":true,"flags":{"swade":{"expiration":null,"loseTurnOnHold":false}},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.p00apKW5V2grVRw2"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The adventurer seems to be blessed by fate, karma, the gods, or whatever external forces he believes in (or believe in him!). </span></p>\n<p>He draws one extra @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.NUjlHH5PBpH1dlzH#bennies]{Benny} at the beginning of each game session, allowing him to succeed at important tasks more often than most, and survive incredible dangers.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172140,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"FAHS1VAcWXUUofaP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"_id":"FBSbqQg7fpr4ouLM","name":"Combat Prowess","type":"edge","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/bust-carved-stone.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kouunmqxeo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Glory Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>Times may be taken: </strong>2</p>\n<p>While most stories about heroes start of close to the truth, they quickly spiral out of control, attributing heroes with abilities far in excess of what they actually possessed.</p>\n<p>The character may take a Combat Edge immediately. He must meet all the requirements as normal.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Glory Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"20+ Glory"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172668,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Roar","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[{"_id":"zlQg0Cnkg8cDuOsp","changes":[{"key":"system.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Block","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.HBNdlqoSuo47ToyJ"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Powerful lungs, magical ability, or great size allow the being to issue a great, boneshaking roar! As a limited action, the character can make an Intimidation @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.z8VbTEJUItMTSxNw]{Test} in a @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.OPSttc2CAS2LC1ju.JournalEntryPage.CvRlxgap3bhXhnqA]{Cone Template}. All targets within are affected and must resist separately.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172464,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"FKX0EnIerosIRnWd","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Sunder","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-life-soul-purple.webp","effects":[{"_id":"zlQg0Cnkg8cDuOsp","changes":[{"key":"system.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Block","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.HBNdlqoSuo47ToyJ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_nsyr9ljpuke","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Species Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Dwarves have an instinctual knowledge of materials. Those with this Edge know just where to strike objects or armored foes to cause the most damage. Any weapon in the hands of a dwarf with this Edge ignores 1 point of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]{armor} (in addition to any @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} value the weapon may already have) on a successful hit. If the dwarf gets a raise on the attack roll, he ignores 2 points of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]{armor}. The Edge applies against all forms of armor, natural or magical. </p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Dwarf"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173283,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"FO7MtnpokCWL0dIK","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"weapon","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_71epj3xngpj","name":"Edges","color":"#008000","folderPath":[],"children":["temp_ce260dx4lpo","temp_wbd74crjrma","temp_gpnez7cqj7","temp_u9f0tp9vn2","temp_nsyr9ljpuke","temp_2i5x75676ju","temp_j9emv9z81ds","temp_fsvlz5d67ma","temp_lfv57yk1te","temp_yg4ulkebj5","temp_kouunmqxeo","temp_ueibkknhw27","temp_tbo7kidroy"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":[],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/weapon.svg","system":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipStatus":1,"isArcaneDevice":false,"arcaneSkillDie":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"powerPoints":{},"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"bonusDamageDie":6,"favorite":false,"templates":{"cone":false,"stream":false,"small":false,"medium":false,"large":false},"category":"","damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"parry":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0,"ammo":"","autoReload":false,"trademark":0,"isHeavyWeapon":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.1.7","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674243562864,"modifiedTime":1674243955399,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"FTOLPlsI7unLrrGQ"}
{"name":"Favored Terrain","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.WJWhWMT8RhtaJjqt"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Rangers, druids, and those who spend great amounts of time in the wilderness know how to use it to their advantage.</p>\n<p>Choose a terrain type (Arctic, Aquatic, Desert, Forest, Hill/Mountain, Jungle, Plains, Swamp, Urban, or Underground). The character draws an additional @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.b0BBoKY0d5GZgOVk]{Action Card}&nbsp;for initiative when in his Favored Terrain. He may then choose from all possible @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.b0BBoKY0d5GZgOVk]{Action Cards}&nbsp;as usual.</p>\n<p>Additionally, the character adds a +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.QwL1xSthAdQEK60D]{Survival} checks made within the chosen favored terrain. They ignore movement penalties for @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#movement]{Difficult Ground} through chosen types of terrain.</p>\n<p>Favored Terrain may be taken multiple times, adding a new Favored Terrain each time.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Survival d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Copanion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172083,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"FX3jlJbvzcaNMBnl","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Rope Monkey","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Rope Monkeys are those sailors who may as well have been born in the rigging. They always seem to know just the right rope to cut and pull to swing to some other part of the ship and can ride the lines down to avoid an otherwise nasty fall.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkey has two functions. The first is to allow a character on the exterior of the ship to move to any other exposed part of the ship by swinging from the rigging. This counts as the character's movement and requires a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll. If successful, he moves to any other external area of the ship. He may not move further this action even by \"running.\" With a raise, he can move and gains momentary surprise on any foes, adding +2 to any @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attacks and damage rolls for the round. This can also be combined with a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test} maneuver.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkeys may also use this ability in forests with tall trees. In that case, the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll is made at &minus;2 and the character may reposition himself within d10\".</p>\n<p>A foe who wants to take his free attack at a Rope Monkey swinging out of melee must subtract 2 from his roll. The same applies to characters with @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.First Strike]{First Strike}&mdash;they suffer a &minus;2 penalty to their @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkeys may also make a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll any time they fall from a ship's rigging (and are conscious). Success means they take half the usual @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Falling]{falling} damage by grabbing onto ropes as they tumble. With a raise, the sailor manages to slide down a rope and suffers no damage.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Athletics d10+"},"grants":[],"source":"50 Fathoms"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173081,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"FZIL3WhC1wRmM9tA","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
