{"name":"Improvisational Fighter","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.QrVqnZrQsZQk9cqu"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Heroes often find themselves fighting with pieces of equipment or furnishings not designed for combat. A brawler with this Edge has a knack for using such improvised weapons. He ignores the usual -2 penalty when wielding them. See </span><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Improvised Weapons]{Improvised Weapons} </span></strong>for more details</span>.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172387,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"FfpouQlv6JrWoW5y","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Two-Weapon Fighting","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>If a character makes an attack with one action and another from a different hand in a later action, the second attack doesn&rsquo;t inflict a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} penalty.</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Off-Hand Attacks]{Off-Hand} penalty still applies unless he&rsquo;s @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ambidextrous]{Ambidextrous}, however.</p>\n<p>The character can choose to make a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attack with each hand, an @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing) attack with each hand, or a combination of these, depending on the readied weapons.</p>\n<p class=\"example\"><strong>Example:</strong> A fighter wields a longsword in one hand and a dagger in the other. He has Two-Weapon Fighting so he rolls @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} on one action with the sword, and then makes a second @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll&mdash;or an @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing) roll&mdash; with the dagger, with no @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action}&nbsp;penalty to either.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172531,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"Fk7h9WOsyy1eaVlo","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Soul Drain","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.IYSNsiuFEYQ1xNos"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Desperate times call for desperate measures. Once per day, Soul Drain allows an arcane character to channel her physical energy into power, taking a level of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} to recover up to five Power Points. She can take an additional level of Fatigue (to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Exhaustion}) to recover up to five more Power Points. She cannot render herself @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Incapacitated} in this way. </span></p>\n<p>Fatigue incurred by Soul Drain comes from deep within and may </span>only </span>be recovered naturally. The <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Relief]{relief}</em></span> </span>power and similar abilities have no effect.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d8+, Arcane Background (Any) or Mystic Powers (Any)"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172987,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"FqVvRei8l0rClNJr","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Shield Wall","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[{"_id":"zlQg0Cnkg8cDuOsp","changes":[{"key":"system.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Block","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.HBNdlqoSuo47ToyJ"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Trained soldiers can stand against overwhelming odds and furious hordes with discipline, training, and a sturdy shield.</p>\n<p>Characters with the Shield Wall Edge (and at least a medium shield) add +1 to their @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.idEEdHIeNSogKRGm]{Parry} if they are adjacent to one ally who also has the Shield Wall Edge, and +2 if they have two adjacent allies with that Edge (the maximum bonus).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Formation Fighter, Fighting d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172471,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"FvtZLYbsf0o8b6H6","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Opportunistic","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[{"_id":"zlQg0Cnkg8cDuOsp","changes":[{"key":"system.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Block","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.HBNdlqoSuo47ToyJ"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Opportunity is what one makes of it. When a character with this Edge is dealt a Joker, he adds +4 to his Trait and damage rolls instead of +2.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172448,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"Fw6rW3qVcPUnK3Jk","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Silent Caster","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Qt3tD20Pgq0u9P9k"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The character has learned how to cast spells or invoke miracles without speaking. She may cast underwater, in a vacuum, while gagged, within a <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.9ViwFVILmCFermGz]{silence}</em> spell, etc.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Any but Bard), Arcana d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172984,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"G90cjq9VB54qt8VR","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"_id":"GMOZnVrAetK0xHRz","name":"Immortalized in Song","type":"edge","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/bust-carved-stone.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kouunmqxeo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Glory Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>Times may be taken: </strong>1</p>\n<p>Whether a brave warrior, a noble lord, or a powerful spellcaster, the character's place in history is assured for eternity. Songs are sung and poems told about his legendary deeds, parents name their children after the hero, and he is welcomed at any goodly settlement. When he eventually dies, he is guaranteed a burial befitting the greatest of heroes.</p>\n<p>The number of Followers the hero currently has doubles, as men flock to bask in his glory (this cannot be applied to Followers gained later). He may also take another Novice @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sidekick]{Sidekick} immediately.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Glory Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic Status taken 4 times"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172696,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Filthy Rich","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This fortunate individual is inordinately wealthy. He starts with 1,500 gp and has a weekly income of [[/r 2d4]] x 1,000 gp. Responsibilities increase dramatically as well, as such wealth requires a staff to manage the business, advisors, or a sizable retinue to take care of day-to-day matters, personal affairs, and other needs.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Rich"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172099,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"GOrmqBAe0ZF7K8RZ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Free Runner","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.DcWv6OHOXjLwc3iN"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your character practices &ldquo;parkour&rdquo; or is just very skilled at running, jumping, swinging, scampering up walls, and over obstacles. </span></p>\n<p>As long as there are obstacles she can bound on, bounce off, or swing on, she moves at her full @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#movement]{Pace} on @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#movement]{Difficult Ground} when on foot. She also adds +2 to her @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls when climbing and in foot </span><strong>Chases </span></strong>(see <strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases &amp; Vehicles}</strong></span>).</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Athletics d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172280,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"GrTSliWotIBVoWzu","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Uncanny Reflexes","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.mTY5axyUKXjsEmmx"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The character has an uncanny ability to avoid area attacks and effects. She ignores the usual &minus;2 @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Agility} penalty when making @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.ZQs1BaqxvPq86odR]{Evasion} attempts. She also gets a regular @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.ZQs1BaqxvPq86odR]{Evasion} attempt against area effect attacks or effects that don&rsquo;t usually allow it (at the usual &minus;2 penalty) such as <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.mK0tJHKFKIeyarLg]{burst}</em> or <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.xJxrn9AfGtpqfhll]{blast}</em>, or even <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.rTXb5MNFDz1d3CkZ]{confusion}</em> or similar spells cast with the Area Effect modifier.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Agility d8+, Athletics d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173119,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"HOj1jwF4JWlcLS3T","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Homunculus","type":"edge","img":"icons/commodities/tech/tube-chamber-lightning.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The artificer gains a magical animated homunculus companion that serves as his familiar. This works exactly as the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.iNjX3XpoWt1uXGjf]{Familiar} Edge.</p>\n<p>The artificer can choose from the available homunculi:</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Arbalaster]{Arbalaster}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Dedicated Wright]{Dedicated Wright}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Expeditious Messenger]{Expeditious Messenger}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Furtive Filcher]{Furtive Filcher}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Iron Defender]{Iron Defender}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary.Packmate]{Packmate}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Artificer)"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171831,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"HRQ7kLGlmApKJUwE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Summoner)","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/orb-hands-humanoid-yellow.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.AiuViCNsPg67wXyk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2i5x75676ju","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Summoner)]{Arcane Background (Summoner)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171700,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"I9yHzewejSRICDph","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Ambidextrous","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.puXQo0wQkTmzT9nQ"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your warrior is as deft with his left hand as he is with his right. He ignores the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Off-Hand Attacks]{Off-Hand Penalty}</p>\n<p>If holding a weapon in each hand, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ambidextrous]{Ambidextrous} characters may stack @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Parry} bonuses (if any) from both weapons.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171955,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"IXOoGidE3sIALfjU","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mark of Shadow","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast one of the following spells:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);\"><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{darkness}</em></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);\"><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{disguise}</em></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);\"><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{illusion}&nbsp;</em>(no Deadly Illusion)</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise} </em><span style=\"background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);\">are </span>self only, but the heir gains no benefit from the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The heir has 10 dedicated Power Points that recharge normally. She automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} for 2 additional Power Points. She may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Phiarlan]{Mark of Shadow} doesn't grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the heir also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or Power Points can be used with the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Phiarlan]{Mark of Shadow} (and vice-versa).</p>\n<p>Additionally, pick any one of the following skills: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth}, and add +1 to the total whenever they are used.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Elf"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172647,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"IgNFn1aWxIaGzm1p","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Inspire","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u9f0tp9vn2","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.lqZDRrfOEGi34gLg"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Exceptional leaders inspire those around them to great feats of valor and determination. Once per turn, the hero may roll his @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} skill to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} one type of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait roll}, and apply it to </span>all </span>allied @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} in @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Command Range}. A leader could Support all @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attacks in range, for example, or all @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Spirit} rolls to recover from being @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}.<br /></span></p>\n<p>Inspire is an @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{action} and requires some sort of communication with those it affects.</span></p>\n<div class=\"sweb-core\"><img src=\"modules/swade-core-rules/assets/art/pg45_quote_edges.webp\" alt=\"&quot;One of my favorites&quot; -- Gabe\" width=\"534\" height=\"120\" /></div>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Leadership Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172772,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"Iy5LVRD1L1dck9uI","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Ace","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.uZSxRkVLgxzgUxxR"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Aces are pilots and drivers who have a special affinity with their lightning rail, boat, or other vehicle. They ignore two points of penalties to any @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.NPJ6q1UWxrTZ5uyn]{Boating} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.FkWqctueXedn6YtI]{Piloting} roll, and may spend @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.RkejkA1MLhB8IeFe]{Bennies} to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.CJOnuNywSJDpO7hK]{Soak} damage for any vehicle they control or command, using the appropriate @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.NPJ6q1UWxrTZ5uyn]{Boating} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.FkWqctueXedn6YtI]{Piloting} skill instead of Vigor. Each success and raise negates a Wound.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173003,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"J3yRSRa3tz1tnnx0","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Explorer","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.RfRuBPxClLL1aPSK"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The world is vast, and this wanderer is called to discover its uncharted reaches. When using the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.lCzNeuOuOqnkWF6E]{Travel} rules (see Savage Worlds), the Explorer may make a Survival roll to draw an additional card from the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.b0BBoKY0d5GZgOVk]{Action Cards} (or two additional cards with a raise) and choose which to use.</p>\n<p>In addition, the Explorer and his party reduces&nbsp;&nbsp;@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.lCzNeuOuOqnkWF6E]{Travel Times} by 10 percent.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d6+, Survival d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173031,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"Jmz2TBu61SbEeuwm","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Heirloom","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.WJWhWMT8RhtaJjqt"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Occasionally, powerful magic items wind up in the hands of relatively novice adventures. This Edge grants your hero one magic item (or a themed set, DM's call) chosen from the magical items with a total value of 10,000 gold pieces each time this Edge is taken.</p>\n<p>This is a one-time only benefit&mdash;if the item is destroyed or is a consumable (like a potion), it isn&rsquo;t replenished. If it&rsquo;s lost, it must be recovered through adventure!</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172119,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"K2IphMq4FwfWIn5V","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Destroy Undead","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-grey.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The undead are abominations to good clerics. The dead have passed on to their just rewards and should not return to the land of the living. It is little wonder then that these holy men and women are so often called to stand against the raging hordes of the undead.</p>\n<p>Evil clerics can also destroy those undead creatures that stand in their path. Perhaps it is their affinity with unnatural things, or perhaps their deity simply grants the power to clear their servants&rsquo; path to greater mayhem.</p>\n<p>As a limited action, the champion spends one Power Point to channel positive energy in a @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.OPSttc2CAS2LC1ju.JournalEntryPage.CvRlxgap3bhXhnqA]{Large Blast Template} centered on herself. Every undead creature within the template automatically takes 2d6 damage (or 3d6 damage for two Power Points).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Cleric)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171782,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"K7YdeZJs3H2eaRL9","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Dead Shot","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.5Rqd7XMiW2PcFzpt"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>When your @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#action-cards-(initiative)]{Action Card} is a Joker, double the total damage of your first successful @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing) or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} roll this round.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Athletics or Shooting d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172236,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"K8oQ8JWeZj2OHd0g","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Adaptable Caster","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Magic is varied and wonderful, and wizards are exposed to countless tomes, scrolls, and incantations as they master their craft. Sometimes they use this knowledge to recall variations of their various enchantments.</p>\n<p>A Wizard can spend 1 extra Power Point when casting a power to change its @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.URSgjRYJvOeHkDtt]{Trapping}. A fireball (<em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Blast]{blast}</em>) might manifest as a lightning bolt, for example. This can often have important consequences if a foe has a particular resistance or weakness to the spell's usual Trapping.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Artificer, Necromancer, Shaman, Summoner, Warlock/Witch, Wizard), arcane skill d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172873,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"KCWZIjCrh45yqjJE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"No Mercy","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.uFRsj7mVMeIABasy"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>When this killer spends a @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.NUjlHH5PBpH1dlzH#bennies]{Benny} to reroll damage, he adds +2 to his final total.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172439,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"KEKpaSQwR34cBhix","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Illusionist)","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/orb-hands-humanoid-yellow.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.6ak50axz9H7wzyf6"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2i5x75676ju","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Illusionist)]{Arcane Background (Illusionist)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171652,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"KROo4j6B83FZMXLj","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mercy","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-grey.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As an action, the character can grant &ldquo;Mercy&rdquo; to any character within a Range equal to her @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Spirit}, automatically removing one of the following states: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.V7Z5r3YBhotQNciO]{Distracted}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.V7Z5r3YBhotQNciO]{Vulnerable}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.fN6mUVj1Lkxtr9HE]{Shaken}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Cleric)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171872,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"KT9he0lKyeXGUZUR","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Master of Arms","type":"edge","img":"icons/sundries/flags/banner-symbol-axe-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fsvlz5d67ma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.qfs7tKIrr7WsX9aw"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Increase the hero's @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Parry} an additional +1 and his @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} bonus damage die is now a d10.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Legendary Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Weapon Master"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172832,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"KebjTgDwfffDZEWs","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Greater Mark of Scribing","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast the additional following power:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{confusion}</em>&nbsp;(spoken or written words trapping only)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>She may now also access any Epic Power modifiers to any powers offered by his dragonmark.</p>\n<p>Additionally the dragonmarked heir gains 5 more Power Points for her dragonmarked powers.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Mark of Scribing"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172587,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"KyQMue5ZyxWKGaQZ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Born in Battle","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_u9f0tp9vn2","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A good grasp of terrain and tactics, as well as knowledge of military history and enemy forces, can bring a general victory even when his troops are inferior to his enemy's. The character gets +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle} rolls. In addition, he gains a +2 bonus to all @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls concerning military matters.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Leadership Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Command, Battle d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172731,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"L0MvBdY93Vxjb45Z","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Ground Fighter","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero does not suffer @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Parry]{Parry} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll reductions when @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Prone]{prone}. If engaged in melee against an opponent who is also @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Prone]{prone}, the hero adds +1 to his @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (if @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Grappling]{Grappling}) or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} rolls.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility or Strength d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172289,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"LHZdEyI2yvGaAshU","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Chi","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ueibkknhw27","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.rwMVsIse7ccC3sUf"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your hero's martial arts training goes beyond the norm and into the realm of the mystical. At the start of each combat encounter, she gains a &ldquo;Chi Point&rdquo; that can be spent to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Reroll one of her failed attacks (even a Critical Failure).</li>\n<li>Make an enemy discard an attack against her, then reroll it from scratch.</li>\n<li>Add +d6 damage to a successful @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack made with her hands, feet, claws, or other @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons} (this may @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Ace}).</li>\n<li>When a monk hits a target with an Unarmed Strike and scores a raise, he may make the foe @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.V7Z5r3YBhotQNciO]{Distracted or Vulnerable}. This occurs even if the victim takes no damage or Soaks it (the states are applied after the victim attempts to Soak).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Unspent Chi is lost at the end of the combat encounter.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Weird Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Martial Warrior"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173321,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"LPr316KbegKSPgDP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mystic Powers (Fighter)","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Qt3tD20Pgq0u9P9k"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>In worlds where magic is relatively common, disciplined adventurers may learn a few simple powers to help them in their quests. Choose one of the packages below. The character has 10 dedicated Power Points that recharge normally. As a limited free action, the hero automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a raise for an additional 2 Power Points. She may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).</p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges that require an Arcane Background, but she may take the Power Points or Soul Drain Edge. If the hero also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges or abilities can be used with Mystic Powers and viceversa.</p>\n<p>Abilities noted as &ldquo;Self Only&rdquo; do not get any additional benefit from that Limitation.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Aii4dhYLbc4Xf8mf]{Boost Trait}</em> (<em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.SzVzIV8ZxqKg3Oe3]{Athletics}</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.MIvf1ckXhEyM27uv]{Fighting}</em>, <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.L2Z2vXl1K5GMZCXm]{Shooting}</em>, <em>Strength</em>, or <em>Vigor</em> only)</li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.KdYR8YGpA9b66t6U]{Protection}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.hUoU4cSN6b5UmO4f]{Smite}</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>All have the Self Limitation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172947,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"LS6VrUs78omTTmRG","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"A Few Good Men","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_u9f0tp9vn2","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}. The character knows how to get the best from the troops at his disposal.</p>\n<p>Once the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Mass Battles]{tokens} for each force have been calculated, the character adds one token to his army's total to account for their status.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Leadership Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Smarts d8+, Inspire, Battle d10+"},"grants":[],"source":"Hellfrost"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172719,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"LV1EO2ApPcNPDiy8","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Martial Artist","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.6OBT6Kt7CWBzIsab"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The fighter has trained in basic martial arts. Her fists and feet are weapons (see </span><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}</strong>) </span>so she's always considered armed. She adds +1 when striking with them and causes @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Strength}+d4 damage. If she already has a Strength damage die from the </span><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Special Ability (Claws)]{Claws} </strong>racial ability or the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brawler]{Brawler} Edge, increase the damage a die type. </span></p>\n<p>Martial Artist does </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">not </span></em>add to damage from other Natural Weapons such as fangs or horns.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172414,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"MIZMGyfBJoINlnmn","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Giant Killer","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.dc17o9tlBMpvEh4H"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The bigger they are, the harder they are to kill. At least for most. Your hero knows how to find the weak points in the most massive of foes. </span></p>\n<p>He adds +1d6 damage when attacking creatures who are three or more Sizes larger than himself (see <strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size}</strong></span>). A human (Size 0) gets the bonus against a creature of Size 3 or greater.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172286,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"MYRu7SMkYmXHaM0r","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Scamper","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-life-soul-purple.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nsyr9ljpuke","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Species Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Halflings are small and quick. Some make great use of this in combat too, scampering about to avoid the blows of larger foes. Opponents of man-size or larger subtract 1 from attack rolls against halflings with this Edge. The benefit only applies when the character is aware the attack is coming, he is unbound and able to move freely, and has no encumbrance penalty.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Halfling, Agility d8+"},"grants":[]},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173268,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"MneZdKfdIPuENjog","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Stone Cunning","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.uZSxRkVLgxzgUxxR"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Those who spend their lives around worked stone quickly perceive imperfections or alterations within its design. Assuming they can see or feel the work, they get one free @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.PQJiYUSX6MD02KkQ]{Notice} roll at +2 to detect traps, hidden doors, or compartments in stonework within 10 feet of their person. Success means they know some alteration has been made, and a raise gives them insight into its general purpose.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Repair d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173101,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"NmhPd6trJ51VUBru","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Power Surge","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.dbwgLVWUDG9yqpq8"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The character recovers 10 Power Points when his @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#action-cards-(initiative)]{Action Card} is a Joker. This may not exceed his usual limit</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Arcane Background (Any), arcane skill d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172982,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"OEVm4Jyo0CvHaQWJ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Ship's Carpenter","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The character may use his knowledge of carpentry to repair damage to a ship without taking it to a dry dock. The ship must still be @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Careening]{careened}, however.</p>\n<p>Repairing each wound requires a successful @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} roll, takes 1d4 days, and requires a half cargo space worth of timber per wound. With a failure the time and materials are ruined. With a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise}, the time is halved. A number of crew equal to the ship's base Toughness are required. Time can be halved with double the crew, or time is doubled every time that number is halved.</p>\n<p>Critical wounds require a successful @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} (&ndash;2) roll and take 1d6 days to fix.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Boating d6+, Repair d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"50 Fathoms"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173089,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ORFPjCJjyoJ8Trhz","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Improved Trademark Weapon","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[{"_id":"Veo3U3jhxpJr1X36","changes":[{"key":"system.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"2","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Imp Trademark Readied Weapon","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Ka1UYVFfYaOcDp7b"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero knows one unique weapon (Excalibur, Old Betsy, Sting) like the back of his hand. When using it, he adds <strong>+2</strong> to his @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls, and <strong>+2</strong> to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Characters]{Parry} when readied (even if it's a ranged weapon).</span></p>\n<p>A fighter can take this Edge multiple times, applying it to a different weapon each time. If a Trademark Weapon is lost, he can replace it but the benefits don't kick in for a few days (however long the DM feels is dramatically appropriate).</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Trademark Weapon"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172383,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ORxsL7cAsMYuL5eH","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Sneak Attack","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.HBNdlqoSuo47ToyJ"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The +2 bonus from the Assassin Edge is replaced by a d6, which may Ace as usual. This applies to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.SzVzIV8ZxqKg3Oe3]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.MIvf1ckXhEyM27uv]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.L2Z2vXl1K5GMZCXm]{Shooting} attacks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Assassin"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172480,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"OcGZItLm5KBuCqbI","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Counterattack","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.L7qkuQIpzpxvTyXF"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fighters with this Edge deal instant punishment for an enemy's mistakes. Once per round (if not @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.OPSttc2CAS2LC1ju.JournalEntryPage.37hOhcNkT98KKtAv]{Stunned}</span>), the character receives a </span><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Attacks]{Free Attacks} </strong></span> against one failed @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack against him. The counterattack takes place immediately (before other hits against the hero on the same @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#action-cards-(initiative)]{Action Card}, if any)</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172234,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"OegsqPMjHBUDtrwa","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Greater Mark of Making","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast the additional following power:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</em> has the range of touch only, but the heir gains no benefit from the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>He may now also access any Epic Power modifiers to any powers offered by his dragonmark.</p>\n<p>Additionally the dragonmarked heir gains 5 more Power Points for his dragonmarked powers.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Mark of Making"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172581,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"OkarkDyXfem6mdBX","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Quick","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[{"_id":"30qhlxEibLwyQU8H","changes":[{"key":"system.initiative.hasQuick","mode":5,"value":"True","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","label":"Quick","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.XHguf9iQ3N9yHN4Z"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Quick characters have lightning-fast reflexes and a cool head. Whenever you are dealt an @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#action-cards-(initiative)]{Action Card} of Five or lower, you may discard it and draw again until you get a card higher than Five.</span></p>\n<p>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Characters} with both the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Level Headed]{Level Headed} and Quick Edges first draw their additional card and choose which to take. If that card is a Five or less, the Quick Edge may be used to draw a replacement until it's Six or higher.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172151,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"P1Qi0dCBRQ6P7sjt","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Soul Jar","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/death/hand-dirt-undead-zombie.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The necromancer&rsquo;s mastery over the dark arts has finally allowed him to cheat death by hiding his soul. Doing so turns the necromancer Undead, though he may continue to look alive and well for the duration of his natural lifespan. Eventually, however, time takes its toll, and the necromancer&rsquo;s true state becomes visible.</p>\n<p>Choose a small to medium size vessel: a gemstone, a statuette, skull, vase, sword, etc. to act as the soul&rsquo;s container. If the necromancer is slain, the soul inhabits a new corpse 2d6 days later. If the vessel is destroyed, the soul is destroyed as well, so most necromancers hide their soul jars in a vault or other secure location.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Arcane Background (Necromancer), Arcana d10+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171900,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"PdF6BdJzqeeh2TGC","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
