{"_id":"WAjNjE53dOVkSTZ8","name":"Streetwise","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tbo7kidroy","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.9dkUUjYdfSoYx10K"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Streetwise characters know how to find the local black market, fence stolen goods, avoid the local law (or criminal element!), lay low when the heat's on, obtain illegal weapons, find out which &ldquo;boss&rdquo; is hiring muscle, or similar shady activities.</p>\n<p>Streetwise characters add +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls made to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} with shady or criminal elements.</p>\n<p>They also add +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls pertaining to the types of disreputable activities listed above.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Social Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173197,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Deadly Illusion","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-slit-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The caster may take the Deadly Power Modifier for their illusions at no additional Power Point cost.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Illusionist), Spellcasting d10+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171771,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"WzQWDSXQH1h0R0Aj","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Arcane Resistance","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.7PSf45taDRsv70Df"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Magic and the supernatural hold little sway with this individual. Whether by nature, heritage, or training he's particularly resistant to magic, psionics, weird science, and other supernatural energies.</p>\n<p>Arcane skills targeting the hero suffer a <strong>-2</strong> penalty (even if cast by allies!) and magical damage is reduced by<strong> 2</strong> as well. This includes magical bonuses granted to weapons, such as the <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.hUoU4cSN6b5UmO4f]{smite}</em> power or the damage bonus of magical weapons.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171968,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"X5oLk02hIrrdO56T","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Savagery","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[{"_id":"zlQg0Cnkg8cDuOsp","changes":[{"key":"system.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Block","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.HBNdlqoSuo47ToyJ"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Violence is a way of life for some. Those with this Edge hit their foes hard enough that they often don&rsquo;t get to reply in kind.</p>\n<p>A character with this Edge causes +4 damage when making a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.xJpg68BZwGvRe0pQ]{Wild Attack} rather than +2.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172468,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"X7KuTS4h6fJgPLLg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Soldier","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[{"_id":"ttN49pTsWkqLr6Ok","changes":[{"key":"system.attributes.strength.encumbranceSteps","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","label":"Soldier","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.j7gnxj7I15IpqIL3"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Professional soldiers get used to carrying heavy loads, and enduring harsh conditions. After a few days getting used to their gear (DM's call), they treat their @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Strength} as one die type higher when determining <strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Gear Notes]{Encumbrance}</strong></span><strong> </span></strong>and </span><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Minimum Strength]{Minimum Strength} </span></strong>to use armor, weapons, and equipment without a penalty. (This stacks with the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brawny]{Brawny} Edge.)<br /></span></p>\n<p>They also get a free reroll on @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Vigor} rolls made to survive environmental hazards (see </span><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Hazards]{Hazards}</span></strong>).</span> <br /><br /></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Vigor d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173098,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"XC8pMnXovmNwlU7A","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Fast Healer","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.6YSd1p2BTIIhDZus"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Those with this blessing add +2 to @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Vigor} rolls for natural healing, and check every three days instead of five (see </span><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing}</span></strong>).</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172069,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"XdI3tZNl4cqPEFGM","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"_id":"Y3DBqbB0yJ39GccX","name":"Heroic Status","type":"edge","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/bust-carved-stone.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kouunmqxeo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Glory Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>Times may be taken: </strong>4</p>\n<p>This bonus represents how well known the hero is across Khorvaire. With heroes few and far between in the modern era, those who stand out from the crowd are widely recognized for their notable deeds.</p>\n<p>Common folk recognize the hero for his brave deeds and are likely to help him in his endeavors, if only for the bragging rights.</p>\n<p>He gains a +1 bonus to initial rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} when dealing with civilized races with whom he has a generally positive reputation, and to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} and @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Networking]{Networking} rolls each time he receives this perk, to a maximum of +4. This stacks with bonuses from any Professional Edges.</p>\n<p>A hero also gains the same bonus to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} rolls&mdash;enemies quake at his name and even allies are fearful of the character's prowess.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Glory Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"20+ Glory"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172688,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"_id":"YExVhGpbOFCchDl6","name":"Followers (Glory)","type":"edge","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/bust-carved-stone.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kouunmqxeo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Glory Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>Times may be taken: </strong>10</p>\n<p>Famous heroes attract entourages and hangers-on. The hero gains the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Followers]{Followers} Edge regardless of his character Rank. The DM and player should work together to determine the nature of the Followers, based on the character's profession and deeds.</p>\n<p>Followers are not automatically replaced when they die. Additional Followers may be gained at Legendary as normal through taking the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Followers]{Followers} Edge with advances or by earning more Glory and taking this benefit.</p>\n<p>Followers don't automatically leave if a character's Glory drops below the level he gained this benefit, but they begin to grumble, refuse orders, and eventually mutiny. In game terms, the character's Leadership Edges no longer work on them. When his Glory rises above the threshold again, his Followers stop grumbling.</p>\n<p>As noted previously in this chapter, having Extras accompany you on every mission means you have to slay more foes to earn Glory.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Glory Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"40+ Glory"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172682,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Eldritch Inspiration","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/air/air-smoke-casting.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Great wizards gather esoteric information in their spellbooks, allowing them to harness magical powers at a whim. Assuming he has his spellbook on his person, the wizard can spend a @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.NUjlHH5PBpH1dlzH#bennies]{Benny} to cast any power of his @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Rank} or lower. The power may be maintained normally but afterwards is forgotten (the wizard doesn't add it to his list of powers).</p>\n<p>A wizard may not use this ability if his spellbook is taken away.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Arcane Background (Wizard)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171790,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"YHlJbMiJ8WmA8BNR","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Greater Mark of Healing","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast the additional following power:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Accelerate Healing]{accelerate healing}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Resurrection]{resurrection}</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>He may now also access any Epic Power modifiers to any powers offered by his dragonmark.</p>\n<p>Additionally the dragonmarked heir gains 5 more Power Points for his dragonmarked powers.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Mark of Healing"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172567,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"YKYOcnAjnZaoFLN5","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Very Attractive","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.b4WY2AZZHq9Jg0hr"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your hero is drop-dead gorgeous. He increases his @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance} and @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} bonus to +2.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Attractive"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172169,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"YbYOGWRcpMa7JjNx","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Channeling","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Z5thwi3zWWr2HXC1"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>When the character gets a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on her @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} roll (or roll to activate or use an @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.qKsVWKzzfAgZAZUx]{arcane devices}), she reduces its Power Point cost by 1. This can take it to 0.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (any)"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172887,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"YgOZuQHPuHisyeej","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Tactician","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u9f0tp9vn2","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.GcxbCSmKxtXpxDzr"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The commander has a natural grasp of small unit tactics and can take advantage of rapidly changing situations. </span></p>\n<p>A Tactician is dealt an extra @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#action-cards-(initiative)]{Action Card} each round of combat or a chase&mdash;kept separate from his own cards. At the start of the round, he may discard it or give it to any one allied @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extra} in @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Command Range}. The player or DM controlling the receiving character can decide whether to accept and replace her current Action Card, or discard it.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Leadership Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Command, Battle d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172799,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"YwR55Qe2xiB80LUn","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Magewright)","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/orb-hands-humanoid-yellow.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_2i5x75676ju","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Magewright)]{Arcane Background (Magewright)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171670,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ZfWTDwdkgZowqMPa","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Charge","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[{"_id":"zlQg0Cnkg8cDuOsp","changes":[{"key":"system.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Block","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.HBNdlqoSuo47ToyJ"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A short burst of speed adds significant impact to this hero&rsquo;s melee damage. If she runs at least 5&rdquo; (10 yards), she adds +2 to the damage of her first @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.MIvf1ckXhEyM27uv]{Fighting} attack that turn. This may be combined with a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.xJpg68BZwGvRe0pQ]{Wild Attack}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172218,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ZpAQO0uZJTpxEUjs","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Unstoppable","type":"edge","img":"icons/sundries/flags/banner-symbol-axe-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fsvlz5d67ma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.C6LLdePT8MWJFhhd"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero is an irresistible force of nature, undaunted by hardship and steadfast in the face of the most seemingly insurmountable obstacles. She has the @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.wQZawcchhTSC6OPq]{Unstoppable} monstrous ability.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Legendary Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary, Vigor d10+, Iron Jaw, Nerves of Steel"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172850,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ZrHJaFSsyJeW475V","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Concentration","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Through training and focus, the caster is extremely efficient in channeling arcane forces. The base Duration of any non-Instant power is doubled. This includes maintaining powers as well.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any) or Mystic Powers (Any)"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172890,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"a528W4yP8LuDS2R2","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Rapid Reload","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.5sylgaYUqEpY9GDI"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The warrior reduces the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reload]{Reload} value of a ranged weapon by 1. This is most often taken for archers using crossbows with a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reload]{Reload} of 1 or 2. Weapons with @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reload]{Reload} 1 may be reloaded as a free action with this Edge.</p>\n<p>A character with this Edge may use Rapid Shot with a weapon if its @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reload]{Reload} value has been reduced to a free action.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shooting d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172450,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"aJ0I7y7PssVmeUTZ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"_id":"aSSRrSKt45XH5bHJ","name":"Skullduggery","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tbo7kidroy","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.hblegBCavI2AaBJu"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your experience has made you skilled in the arts of deception, disguise and skullduggery. The use of clever underhanded actions to achieve any ends is your masterful skill in trade. You get a free reroll to any @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception} check.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Social Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Deception d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173188,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Feint","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Bswysz4o8oSUq4CP"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>When performing a </span><strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test} </span></strong>with the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} skill, you can choose to make the foe resist with @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} instead of @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Agility}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172264,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"aump4nnyanKxm92S","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Improved Sunder","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-life-soul-purple.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nsyr9ljpuke","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Species Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Dwarves have an instinctual knowledge of materials. Those with this Edge know just where to strike objects or armored foes to cause the most damage. Any weapon in the hands of a dwarf with this Edge ignores 2 point of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]{Armor} (in addition to any @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} value the weapon may already have) on a successful hit. If the dwarf gets a raise on the attack roll, he ignores 4 points of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]{Armor}. The Edge applies against all forms of armor, natural or magical.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Sunder"},"grants":[]},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173252,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"b18YAIZe9vKlEj0d","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Followers","type":"edge","img":"icons/sundries/flags/banner-symbol-axe-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fsvlz5d67ma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.vhYwLlPwhocsSM68"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Each time this Edge is chosen, five followers come to fight by the hero's side. If any are lost, others eventually take their place (how long is up to the DM and the circumstances).</p>\n<p>Followers must be cared for and generally want a share of whatever loot, treasure, or other rewards the hero acquires. Otherwise, they are completely dedicated to their task. They won't throw their lives away but are willing to risk them repeatedly in his service.</p>\n<p>Use the <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Soldier]{Soldier} </strong>profile for the followers. A hero may outfit her allies as she sees fit. Followers <strong>@UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Advance} </strong>just like player characters.</p>\n<p>Use the <strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Allies]{Allies} </strong>rules  to give them distinctive personal&shy;ities if desired.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Legendary Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172819,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"bCODi9YcxvBbImdv","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Knight","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Knights pledge fealty to their lord or order, serving as enforcers and most importantly warriors in whatever cause their liege demands. They have whatever authority their lord gives them over common folk in their realm. This is usually limited to food, lodging, and basic services required to fulfill their duties, but with express approval may also include mustering militias, adjudicating disputes, and dispensing justice.</p>\n<p>They represent their liege or order, and such, Knights represent their master, add +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.NWzjRjwyVKIngdAM]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.TY6Vt7W3PY07fKSz]{Persuasion} rolls with those who respect or fear authority.</p>\n<p>If taken during character creation, or with the DM's approval afterward, the hero inherits or is granted a war horse, lance, long sword, a full suit of heavy armor (or medium if preferred), and a medium shield.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Strength d6+, Vigor d6+, Fighting d8+, Riding d6+, Obligation (Major—serve their lord or order)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173047,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"bQwFPi51wqLFPcnf","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Brave","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Gzwdz7rVmp0AmFfJ"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Those with this Edge have learned to master their fear, or have dealt with so many horrors they've become jaded. These valiant explorers add +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks and subtract 2 from </span><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Fear Table} </span></strong>results.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172017,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"bU691YPCq5AKEeJd","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"New Powers","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Qt3tD20Pgq0u9P9k"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>An arcane character may learn two new @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Powers]{powers} by choosing this Edge (which may be taken multiple times). He may choose from any powers of his @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Rank} or lower normally available to his particular @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.7 Arcane Backgrounds & Edges]{Arcane Backgrounds}.<br /></span></p>\n<p>A character can add a new @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.URSgjRYJvOeHkDtt]{Trapping} on a power she already has instead of gaining a new one. She might add an ice Trapping to her existing fire <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Bolt]{bolt}</em></span>, for example, so she could switch between ice and fire Trappings freely</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Any)"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172968,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"baxaDqYcVWLczXfl","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Shifter Stamina","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-life-soul-purple.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nsyr9ljpuke","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Species Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Some shifters can persist with endurance beyond most others. Shifters with this Edge are immune to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Nonlethal Damage]{nonlethal damage}, and the effects of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{fatigue} are suppressed. When their shifting ends, any @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{fatigue} effects that would have taken effect during shifting (or that were in effect when shifting began) take effect normally.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (Any)"},"grants":[]},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173271,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"bj2u4cCnJndvoCwq","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Power Points","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.83p0QZSnEgbmCHKv"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Wizards, weird scientists, and other arcane types always want more power. This Edge grants them an additional 5 Power Points. </span></p>\n<p>Power Points may be selected more than once, but only once per @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Rank}. It may be taken as often as desired at Legendary Rank, but each grants only 2 additional points.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Any) or Mystic Powers (Any)"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172970,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"brBWu9bvtIAkrHFJ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Sacred Fetish","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/nature/root-vines-face-glow-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fetishes are devices that help a shaman focus her powers. A sacred fetish is one that&rsquo;s been blessed or sanctified in some way. As long as she has the fetish in hand or prominently displayed on her person, she gets one free reroll whenever she fails a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.OfnjSxCc2QxHcIhp]{Faith} roll.</p>\n<p>Should a sacred fetish be lost or destroyed, the shaman may replace it by visiting her tribe for some item of sentimental worth or creating a new device that captures the essence of her people.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background, (Shaman), Faith d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171896,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"buK39QI6UL09SGnI","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Thief","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[{"_id":"D9KpAeGji8Bmw29m","changes":[{"key":"@Skill{Thievery}[system.die.modifier]","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":28973116800,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","label":"Thief","transfer":true,"flags":{"swade":{"expiration":null,"loseTurnOnHold":false}},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.lp2OQZTT3w4NuITR"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Thieves specialize in deceit, treachery, and acrobatics. They can be invaluable where traps must be detected, walls must be climbed, and locks must be picked. </span></p>\n<p>Thieves know how to use protrusions on walls and window ledges to climb the tallest of buildings, scampering through streets and back alleys like cats. They add +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls made to climb in urban areas. </span></p>\n<p>Thieves also know how to use the dark areas between the streetlights of cities to conceal their movements, and add +1 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} rolls when in an urban environment. </span></p>\n<p>Finally, these rogues are&mdash;not surprisingly&mdash; adept at @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} itself, adding +1 to those rolls in all circumstances.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Stealth d6+, Thievery d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173104,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"c9g3jPssUUeXYSGC","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Elan","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.fFV91FJDGbRHBoMr"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Elan means energy or spirit. Those who have it rise to the occasion when the going gets toughest. When you spend a @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.NUjlHH5PBpH1dlzH#bennies]{Benny} to reroll a @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Trait}, add +2 to the total. The bonus applies only when rerolling. It doesn't apply to @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#damage]{damage} rolls (since they're not Trait rolls), nor does it apply to @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#soak-rolls]{Soak rolls} unless you're using </span><em>another </span></em>Benny to reroll the @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Vigor} check.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172049,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"cQBs3kKA3cUO13Xe","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Command Presence","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u9f0tp9vn2","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.1zMktaRGijGHjBa7"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A booming voice, effective commands, natural charisma, or simple training results in a much more effective combat element. A hero with this Edge has a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Command Range} of 10&Prime; (20 yards).</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Leadership Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172736,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"cmj9xUyvrkArYuJD","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Beast Talker","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ueibkknhw27","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.2DgugORlrVDyNh1z"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The character can speak to and understand a general class of animals: birds, marine animals (fish, crustaceans, etc.), insects, mammals, reptiles, etc.</p>\n<p>She doesn&rsquo;t control them, but can attempt to persuade them to help or provide whatever information creatures of their type might understand. The DM should impose appropriate modifiers when conversing with pets, hostile or skittish animals, predators, or those animals who have been hunted or preyed upon.</p>\n<p>The vocabularies, memories, and comprehension of such creatures are limited by their type&mdash;a dog knows and understands far more than a fish, for example. The nature of the world may also define how much its animals understand.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Weird Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173316,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"cni913HwwOsJQv7e","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Power Pool","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Z5thwi3zWWr2HXC1"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Characters can have multiple Arcane Backgrounds with the Dungeon Master&rsquo;s permission, though each has its own set of powers and Power Points.</p>\n<p>This Edge lets them combine Power Points from two or more different arcane skills into a single pool. A hero with 10 points in both magic and miracles, for example, could combine them into a single 20 point pool that both may draw from.</p>\n<p>Power Points from the Mystic Powers Edge may not be pooled.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, two Arcane Backgrounds (Any), both arcane skills at d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172973,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"coGLuQPcr9WRH2sR","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"_id":"d3teo8ILU0NoDPhI","name":"Reliable","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tbo7kidroy","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.3nyfzyszGqFIgqjR"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>People know they can depend on your hero when they need assistance. He gets a free reroll on any @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Support]{Support} roll.</span> </p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Social Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173182,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Beast Master","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ueibkknhw27","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.KMuOdy1cMV3cHe0Z"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Animals take to your hero quickly and easily. They won't attack him unless he attacks them first or they're enraged for some reason.</p>\n<p>The Beast Master's &ldquo;animal magnetism&rdquo; is so great he's attracted a loyal animal of some sort as well. This is typically an animal of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} 0 or smaller, subject to the DM's approval. </p>\n<p>The beast is an @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extra} and doesn't @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Advance} in Rank or abilities. If a pet is dismissed or killed, the hero gains a replacement in [[/r 1d4]] days.</p>\n<p><strong>More Powerful Companions</strong>: Beast Master may be taken more than once. Choose one of the effects below each time it's chosen:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Gain an additional pet.</li>\n<li>Increase one of the pet's @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Traits} one die type (only one Trait per pet).</li>\n<li>Increase the maximum Size pet you may have by +1, to a maximum of 3.</li>\n<li>Make one pet a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}. (The hero must be of @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Heroic Rank}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Weird Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173313,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"d9aS339sZq63LgUo","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Trick Shot","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[{"_id":"zlQg0Cnkg8cDuOsp","changes":[{"key":"system.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Block","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.HBNdlqoSuo47ToyJ"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>When performing a Test with the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.SzVzIV8ZxqKg3Oe3]{Athletics} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.L2Z2vXl1K5GMZCXm]{Shooting} skill, the archer can choose to make the foe resist with @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} instead of @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Athletics d8+ or Shooting d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172523,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"dCUDwFmd6KUfZSUY","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"True Form","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/nature/leaf-juggle-humanoid-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>While shape changed, the druid can speak and cast powers at a &ndash;2 penalty even if in a form that usually wouldn&rsquo;t allow</p>\n<p>Some druids essentially &ldquo;live&rdquo; in their animal form, maintaining their bestial shape for days on end. Doing so gradually erodes the druid&rsquo;s humanity. For every day the druid spends more than half her time in animal form, she must make a @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Spirit} roll. Failure reduces her Spirit a die type until she remains in human form for an entire week. If her @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Spirit} is reduced below d4 in this manner, the druid becomes that creature forever.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Druid)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171919,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"dHayGRudkyVYgRCV","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Marksman","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.JwtnQIOFQGVOzHwX"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero is a natural with ranged weapons. If she doesn't move in a turn and fires no more than a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rate of Fire]{Rate of Fire} of 1 as her first action, she may add +1 to an @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing) or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} roll, or ignore up to 2 points of penalties from @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.OPSttc2CAS2LC1ju.JournalEntryPage.FtSdZK9mueD0Pkz0]{Called Shots}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{Cover}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Range]{Range}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Speed]{Speed}. This is a lesser version of the @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.OPSttc2CAS2LC1ju.JournalEntryPage.aMKEcG5KZtdH143K]{Aim} maneuver and does not stack with it. Marksman doesn't apply to additional attacks after the first.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Athletics d8+ or Shooting d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172407,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"dhjKdM4TvY06574R","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Improved Close Fighting","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This Edge is for skilled knife-fighters and pugulists, who pride themselves on defeating their foes up close and personal.</p>\n<p>A Close Fighter armed with a knife or similar small weapon (DM&rsquo;s call) choose a single adjacent target as a free action each turn. Their attacks and @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.idEEdHIeNSogKRGm]{Parry} for that foe (only) increase by the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.PTDRRY03N4bzcRak]{Reach} +2</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Close Fighting"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172305,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"drbvtSo10aH7jCWt","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Acrobat","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.uZSxRkVLgxzgUxxR"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The Acrobat gets one free reroll on @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} totals that involve balance, tumbling, or grappling. It doesn't affect rolls to interrupt actions, climb, swim, or throw.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Athletics d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173006,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"e0IBuheIv73pwwSA","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Primal Fury","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-life-soul-purple.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nsyr9ljpuke","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Species Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>With sufficient willpower, a hero who has learned to trigger his rage can restrain it as well. Primal Fury allows the hero to ignore the &minus;2 penalty to end his rage, and on a Critical Failure, he will not hit an ally while @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} (though he may still hit the wrong opponent or miss).</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Half-orc or Orc, Berserk"},"grants":[]},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173255,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"e1XRuAy0N7jl3r6O","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Berserk","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[{"_id":"WbpbMSny7VbIgquB","changes":[{"key":"system.attributes.strength.die.sides","mode":2,"value":"2","priority":null},{"key":"system.wounds.ignored","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null},{"key":"system.stats.toughness.value","mode":2,"value":"2","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"rounds":10,"turns":10,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","label":"Berserk","transfer":true,"flags":{"swade":{"expiration":2,"loseTurnOnHold":false}},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Berserkers become wild and nearly uncontrollable when the &ldquo;red rage&rdquo; takes them, but they are deadly killing machines as well!</p>\n<p>Immediately after suffering a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound or a Shaken} result (from physical damage only), your hero must make a @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} roll or go Berserk. She can voluntarily fail this check if she likes.</p>\n<p>Going Berserk has the following effects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fury:</strong> The character's Strength increases a die type and every melee attack must be a <strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Attack]{Wild Attack}</strong>. She cannot use any skills that require wit or concentration (DM's call). She may scream out threats and use @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, for example.</li>\n<li><strong>Enraged:</strong>&nbsp; Adrenaline and rage fuel the berserker&rsquo;s muscles, adding +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5 Marking Characters]{Toughness}. She ignores one level of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.ih5SJibOjuXkxey4]{Wound} penalties (this stacks with any other abilities that reduce Wound penalties).</li>\n<li><strong>Reckless Abandon:</strong> Anytime a berserker rolls a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} check, she hits a random target within range of her attack (not the intended target), friend or foe. If there are no applicable targets, the blow simply misses, smashes nearby objects, etc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>After five consecutive rounds of berserk fury, the hero takes a level of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}. At ten rounds, she takes another level of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} and the rage ends. She may also choose to end her rage at any time by making a @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} &ndash;2 roll (as a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action}; possibly avoiding @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} if she manages to end her rage before it's incurred!). Start the count anew if she goes berserk again, even in the same battle.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172007,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"e9o3JTsDwJR3mwom","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
