{"name":"Tough As Nails","type":"edge","img":"icons/sundries/flags/banner-symbol-axe-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fsvlz5d67ma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.ZvTtDC9xDT9vf3rC"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your character keeps going when others fall. She can take four @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} before she's @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated} (her maximum Wound penalty is still &minus;3).</p>\n<p> </p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Legendary Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Vigor d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172840,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"f3YcZIZBtSrrv4xh","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Improved Sweep","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Sweep allows a character to make a single @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack with a two-handed weapon and apply it against all targets in his Reach (friends and foes alike). Resolve damage separately for each enemy that's hit.</p>\n<p>A character or creature may only perform a Sweep once per turn. Sweep may not be combined with @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy} in the same action.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Some creatures have the Sweep Edge even though they don't have two-handed weapons. In their case their size, lanky limbs, or other advantages allow them to make Sweep attacks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Sweep"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172379,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"fTwZivwbrR6oNgOH","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Jack-Of-All-Trades","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.QKXUG2dvJK5efDnC"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Through advanced schooling, book-learning, computer-enhanced skill programs, or just amazing intuitive perception, your hero has a talent for picking up skills on the fly. There's little he can't figure out given a little time and a dash of luck.</span></p>\n<p>The character makes a @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} roll as an action after observing or studying some subject. She gains a d4 in the relevant skill with success, or d6 with a raise. She may try again after an hour of study, trial and effort, or immersion if she fails or wants to try for a raise. This lasts until the character attempts to learn a different subject, whether she's successful or not.</span> <br /></span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d10+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173038,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"fzcoBjUTZgHBKOhB","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Chosen","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.WJWhWMT8RhtaJjqt"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Prophecies tell of a being destined for greatness. One who will, with the help of her boon companions, do great things. When the Chosen spends @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.5r9kaya39Lic4mah]{Conviction}, it lasts until the end of the encounter without having to maintain it with @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.RkejkA1MLhB8IeFe]{Bennies}!</p>\n<p>Of course, such a boon comes at a great cost. The Chosen has the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-hindrances.j9U94aMTNsK1DqSr]{Enemy} (Major) Hindrance&mdash;there&rsquo;s always some powerful being opposed to her quest! Worse, she has a mark of some sort that can&rsquo;t be removed no matter how much she tries. It might be a tattoo, birthmark, sixth finger, catlike pupils, or some other visible cosmetic oddity, but those who know what to look for can find it. And by whatever narrative means necessary, the mark shows through occasionally, regardless how hard she attempts to cover it with clothing, wraps, or even illusions. This means the hero&rsquo;s foe and his minions are always on her trail.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Wild Card"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172038,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"g1H12sEIY9GIN9w8","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"The Witching Hour","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/perception/hand-eye-fire-blue.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.olo05rxG7sk33Bpt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Witches and warlocks are more powerful between the hours of midnight and 1 am (or some other suitable time in your campaign world). During this hour, a witch or warlock cannot @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.hCxcCUCRxHOWcNGS]{Critically Failures} a roll (it&rsquo;s just a normal failure), and gets a free @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.CJOnuNywSJDpO7hK]{Soak roll} anytime she takes a Wound!</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Warlock/Witch)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171915,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"g8C2PFw8Sd7nTKfz","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Alertness","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.WJWhWMT8RhtaJjqt"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Not much gets by this hero. He's very observant and perceptive, and adds +2 to his @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls to hear, see, or otherwise sense the world around him.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171950,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"g9xzqBgAUEdxjROb","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Improved Level Headed","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[{"_id":"R9f6YKS0pO3CPHHO","changes":[{"key":"system.initiative.hasImpLevelHeaded","mode":5,"value":"True","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Imp Level Headed","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.q5CVmMLBKErSsnOS"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fighters who can keep their cool when everyone else is running for @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover} make deadly combatants. A hero with this Edge draws <strong>two</strong> additional @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#action-cards-(initiative)]{Action Cards} in combat and chooses which to use.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Level Headed"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172348,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"gTugIsDIhi5zD4BK","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Spellbooks","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/air/air-smoke-casting.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YHlJbMiJ8WmA8BNR"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A wizard&rsquo;s spellbooks contain copious notes on magical processes, arcane observations, and thaumaturgical insights.</p>\n<p>Whenever he takes the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.baxaDqYcVWLczXfl]{New Powers} Edge, he gets three new powers instead of two.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Wizard)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171902,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"gyqYPac76u7AvQDQ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mentalist","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/holy/meditation-chi-focus-blue.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.P1JDB4fGRew7VBbG"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Constant contact with multiple minds gives these psionic agents an edge when it comes to forcing or resisting mental assaults. </span></p>\n<p>Mentalists add +2 to opposed @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Psionics]{Psionics} rolls, whether they are using their powers against a foe or defending against a rival.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Psionics)"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171869,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"gzv32f6io6DDiF2B","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Level Headed","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[{"_id":"aOlH8icFO8Fl8bfF","changes":[{"key":"system.initiative.hasLevelHeaded","mode":5,"value":"True","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Level Headed","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.D2j0AuKKBKcyGEhS"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Fighters who can keep their cool when everyone else is running for @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover} make deadly combatants. A hero with this Edge draws an additional @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#action-cards-(initiative)]{Action Card} in combat and chooses which to use.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172401,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"h3a83pDlF5U11e1h","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Heartwood Staff","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/nature/leaf-juggle-humanoid-green.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Some druids focus their powers through a staff made from rare wood, such as the heart of a great oak or the last palm from a dying desert oasis.</p>\n<p>If such a staff is lost or broken, the druid must spend at least eight hours in an old forest with at least a few trees a hundred years old or more. There he may make a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.OfnjSxCc2QxHcIhp]{Faith} roll at &ndash;2 once per day to forge another. This sacrifices the tree it&rsquo;s taken from.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">HEARTWOOD STAFF:</span> Str+d8, Min Str d6, Weight 6 lbs., Parry +1, Reach 1, requires two hands. After the druid hits with the staff, he may spend a Power Point to cause an extra d6 damage. This die may Ace.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Druid)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171821,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"h7nBe9Siuv1tAv2R","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Charismatic","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.t9CHSlLks9nQ8lIv"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your hero is likable for some reason. She may be trustworthy or kind, or might just exude confidence and goodwill. You get one free reroll on @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172035,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"hd4SZiC6M49me6Iq","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"University Trained","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>You attended one of the prestigious universities in the world. You like to read, and you absorb the information like a sponge. These books can be found in classrooms, in libraries or even in the local coffee shop. Book Learning confers 4 additional skill points on the Character, but these points must be spent on the following: <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Language]{Language}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Religion]{Religion} </em>or <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Science]{Science}</em>.</p>\n<p>Because of your interest in books, a character with this Edge gains one additional @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Language]{Language} at a d6.</p>\n<p><strong>Special: </strong>This Edge must be taken during character creation or after actually going to one of the schools of Khorvaire with DM approval.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172165,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"hnAuPH0yEYFCL325","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Elemental Absorption","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/elements-air-earth-fire-water.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The elements fill and sustain you. Your Toughness increases by +2 while experiencing elemental synergy (see @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.6ak50axz9H7wzyf6]{Arcane Background (Elementalist)}).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Elementalist)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171801,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"iF4WIpuhXydNWNJs","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Familiar","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Z5thwi3zWWr2HXC1"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>&ldquo;Familiars&rdquo; are small creatures (Size &minus;2 or &minus;3) that serve as a mage&rsquo;s loyal pet and magical companion. They are loyal to their masters but aren&rsquo;t slaves. They are very smart versions of their species and can occasionally be distracted by their own inherent instincts. For example, a cat might interrupt its task to chase a mouse or take a brief nap, and a dog will almost certainly bark when a stranger approaches.</p>\n<p>A familiar is a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.IZ9YJamVRZdr4VVU]{Wild Card} with respect to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.ih5SJibOjuXkxey4]{Wounds} and rolling a Wild Die with its @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Trait rolls}. It doesn&rsquo;t get Bennies, but the mage can spend his own on its behalf.</p>\n<p>The familiar can understand its master&rsquo;s speech and vice-versa (others hear only the creature&rsquo;s natural sounds), though concepts are limited to what a member of its species might understand.</p>\n<p>The familiar has 5 Power Points of its own. It cannot cast spells, but the mage can draw on them as if they were his own. They recharge separately and at the same rate as the mage&rsquo;s.</p>\n<p>The bond between the familiar and the mage makes it immune to the <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.i78Y7jme40GZiRcI]{beast friend}</em> power cast by others.</p>\n<p>Familiars don&rsquo;t advance, but instead gain one of the advantages below for each of its master&rsquo;s @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Ranks} (including Novice) and for every fourth advance the hero gains past Legendary.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">SECOND SIGHT:</span> The owner may use the familiar&rsquo;s senses as if they were her own, with a maximum range of 10 miles. She is @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.V7Z5r3YBhotQNciO]{Distracted and Vulnerable} while doing so.</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">TRAINING:</span> The mage can increase one of the familiar&rsquo;s Traits one die type (no more than once per Trait).</li>\n<li><span class=\"list-heading\">ENHANCEMENT:</span> The familiar gains an Edge. It must make sense for the familiar&rsquo;s species (DM&rsquo;s call) and meet the Requirements as usual.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If a familiar dies, the hero is automatically @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.D2Z390QR9ROJwxMy]{Stunned} (no matter how far away he is). He can summon another after 10 days and can change the type if she chooses.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Druid, Elementalist, Infernalist, Necromancer, Shaman, Sorcerer, Warlock/Witch, Wizard)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172903,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"iNjX3XpoWt1uXGjf","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mark of Sentinel","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast one of the following spells:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{arcane protection}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{protection}</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);\">All powers have the range of touch only, but the heir gains no benefit from the </span>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The heir has 10 dedicated Power Points that recharge normally. He automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} for 2 additional Power Points. He may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Deneith]{Mark of Sentinel} doesn't grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the heir also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or Power Points can be used with the Mark of Sentinel (and vice-versa).</p>\n<p>Additionally, pick any one of the following skills: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}, and add +1 to the total whenever they are used.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Human"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172639,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"iVpC1Y30Ug0QoDyp","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Entertainer","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>You character is skilled in their performing arts: singing, story telling, comedy, acting, sleight of hand, etc. They also adept in speaking before a crowd.</p>\n<p>Pick any two of the following skills: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Deception]{Deception}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Performance]{Performance}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} and add +1 to the total whenever they're used.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be taken more than once if applied to different skills.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Performance d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173022,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ihES5XJf3gdv4Rbn","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Master Tactician","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u9f0tp9vn2","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.qWZMjqFyiwzUolEW"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tactician]{Tactician} now gets a total of two extra @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#action-cards-(initiative)]{Action Cards} to distribute each round</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Leadership Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Tactician"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172783,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ixjD3i3aSBROSIJl","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Hold the Line!","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u9f0tp9vn2","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.m5kYXSHhfA26Ji4F"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Hold the Line strengthens the will of any @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} under the hero's command, adding +1 to their @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Leadership Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Command"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172768,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"jQ1Tu6tKIgsGuujS","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Rich","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Whether the individual was born with a silver spoon in his mouth or earned it through hard work, he's got more money than most.</p>\n<p>Rich heroes start with 900 gold galifars instead of the usual 300. The hero also receives [[/r 1d6+6]] x 100 gp per week, perhaps from family holdings, a profitable business, or an inheritance. Whether he can get to it or not is another matter. It might simply build up in an account, or more likely, as a collection of assets such as a manor or estate. Of course that kind of wealth usually comes with obligations to spend it, pay taxes, or take care of retainers, employees, caretakers, and grounds.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172156,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"jvLa3GcF1ihS9NNb","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Master","type":"edge","img":"icons/sundries/flags/banner-symbol-axe-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fsvlz5d67ma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.cn4vidVwxa9qn9ou"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>The character's Wild Die increases to a d10 when rolling the selected @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Expert]{Expert} Trait.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Legendary Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary, Expert in affected Trait"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172829,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"kVI0G3fyWW8oygLE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
