{"name":"Shifting Recovery","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-life-soul-purple.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nsyr9ljpuke","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Species Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>After shifting ends, the recovery time to remove a level of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue] is halved. This Edge can be taken multiple times, each time halving the recovery time to a minimum of 15 minutes.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (any)"},"grants":[]},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173280,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"lIlyaB230o2ffYv7","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Scout","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_j9emv9z81ds","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.uZSxRkVLgxzgUxxR"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Scouts are masters of navigating the mystic lands of their fantastic worlds. When the Dungeon Master draws a face card while the party is traveling (see the Encounter Rules under @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.lCzNeuOuOqnkWF6E]{Travel} in Savage Worlds) the Scout may make a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.PQJiYUSX6MD02KkQ]{Notice} roll at &minus;2 to detect the hazard, creature, or event first.</p>\n<p>Scouts are always considered alert for @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.PQJiYUSX6MD02KkQ]{Notice} rolls versus @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.lCPTPB1Y1oD2bag0]{Stealth} and add +2 to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.rh7oCZnozOCNsmdo]{Common Knowledge} rolls to recall information about towns, outposts, landmarks, or lairs along a particular route they may have traveled before (player and DM's call).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Professional Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Survival d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173086,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"lOZEoAs1k0bN2zmO","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Instrument","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/trades/music-singing-voice-blue.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1EMcGBXdZi6N5iYA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Singing bards often use musical instruments to accentuate their ballads, striking chords or hitting high notes at particularly inspiring parts of their songs. Dancing bards may use streamers or swords as their instrument of choice, while oratory bards might incorporate elaborate props or masks.</p>\n<p>A bard who uses an instrument of some kind when casting a spell adds +1 to her @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.WeqRVXtog034GUoR]{Performance} roll. The bonus only applies when @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.WeqRVXtog034GUoR]{Performance} is used as an @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill}. Of course the instrument requires one or more hands to play.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Bard)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171849,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"lWVd8UuQ6lN74Wh2","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Improved Arcane Resistance","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/group.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_yg4ulkebj5","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.l5Sr36sbFvktsclb"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Magic and the supernatural hold little sway with this individual. Whether by nature, heritage, or training he's particularly resistant to magic, psionics, weird science, and other supernatural energies.</p>\n<p>Arcane skills targeting the hero suffer a -4 penalty (even if cast by allies!) and magical damage is reduced by 4 as well. This includes magical bonuses granted to weapons, such as the <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.hUoU4cSN6b5UmO4f]{smite}</em> power or the damage bonus of magical weapons.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Background Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Resistance"},"grants":[],"source":"SWADE"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172133,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"lbExx8iOaRHeUyHt","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Psicrystal","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-life-soul-purple.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsyr9ljpuke","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Species Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.P1JDB4fGRew7VBbG"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>A psicrystal is a fragment of a kalashtar's personality, brought into physical form and a semblance of life. It appears as a crystalline construct about the size of a human hand.</p>\n<p><strong>Psicrystal Personalities: </strong>A psicrystal has its own personality (a fragment of the owner's personality), which gives its owner a bonus on certain types of @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Trait} @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Tests}, as given on the table below. These special abilities and bonuses apply only when the owner and the psicrystal are within 1 mile of each other.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Bully:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} checks</li>\n<li><em>Friendly: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} checks</li>\n<li><em>Hero:</em> +1 bonus on @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Vigor} rolls</li>\n<li><em>Nimble:</em> +1 bonus on @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Agility} rolls to interrupt actions</li>\n<li><em>Observant: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice} checks</li>\n<li><em>Resolved:</em> +1 bonus on @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Spirit} rolls</li>\n<li><em>Sage:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore} checks</li>\n<li><em>Single-minded: </em>+1 bonus to @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Psionics]{Psionics} rolls while maintaining powers</li>\n<li><em>Sneaky: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} checks</li>\n<li><em>Sympathetic: </em>+1 bonus on @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smart} rolls</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Each psicrystal has a distinct personality, chosen by its owner at the time of its creation from among those given on the table. Upon taking this Edge, its owner typically gets a feel for a psicrystal's personality only through occasional impulses, but as the owner increases gains experience, the psicrystal's personality becomes more pronounced.</p>\n<p>As the owner advances, it is not uncommon for a psicrystal to constantly ply its owner with observations and advice, often severely slanted toward the psicrystal's particular worldview. The owner always sees a bit of himself in his psicrystal, even if magnified and therefore distorted.</p>\n<p><strong>Psicrystal Advancement:</strong> At each Rank of the owner, the psicrystal has the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Novice:</em> @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor] +1; @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} d4</li>\n<li><em>Seasoned: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]</em> +2; @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} d6</li>\n<li><em>Veteran: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]</em> +3; @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} d8</li>\n<li><em>Heroic: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]</em> +4; @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} d10</li>\n<li><em>Legendary: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor]</em> +5; @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} d12</li>\n</ul>\n<p>A psicrystal can speak one language of its owner's choice (so long as it is a language the owner knows). A psicrystal can understand all other languages known by its owner, but cannot speak them.</p>\n<p>Because of the telepathic link between a psicrystal and its owner, the owner has the same connection to an item or place that the psicrystal does. For instance, if his psicrystal has seen a room, the owner can teleport into that room as if he has seen it too, negating the -4 penalty for the destination being an unknown area; the -2 penalty for not being able to see it presently might still apply.</p>\n<p>The psicrystal is a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} with respect to Wounds and the Wild Die, but has no Prophecy Shards. The owner may spend his for the psicrystal, however.</p>\n<p>Each additional time this Edge is taken, the psion can pick one of the powers below. Each power may only be taken once. The psion may take this Edge only once each Rank. Taking it during character creation allows the psion to take it again while he's a Novice.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The psicrystal gains @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance} against psionics.</li>\n<li>The psion can transfer @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} and @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} levels to or from his psicrystal as a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free actions}.</li>\n<li>The psion can use the psicrystal's senses as if they were his own. This requires concentration. The maximum range for this ability is the psion's @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Smarts} x 100 yards.</li>\n<li>Whenever the psicrystal is adjacent to or in the possession of its owner, the owner has the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Alertness]{Alertness} Edge.</li>\n<li>Any powers the psion manifests on himself also affect the psicrystal. If he manifests armor with a raise, both he and his psicrystal gain +4 @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Armor] for the duration, for example.</li>\n<li>The psicrystal has 5 Power Points, which the psion may use as if they were his own. They recharge at the same rate as the psion's (usually 1 per hour).</li>\n<li>The psicrystal can act as a conduit for the psion's powers by delivering touch powers manifested by its owner. The owner and the psicrystal must be in contact at the time the power is manifested. The power must be delivered before the owner can manifest another power. At @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Legendary} Rank, the owner can manifest the power through the psicrystal to a distance of up to 1 mile.</li>\n<li>At @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.saneNpHYSTivNRYE]{Seasoned} Rank or above, the owner, as a standard action, can will his psicrystal to fly with @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#movement]{Pace} 6. The effect lasts for one day (or until the owner dismisses it, at which point the psicrystal drifts gently to the ground).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If the psicrystal is destroyed, the character must take this Edge again to create a new psicrystal. However, the previous acquisitions of this Edge to add to its abilities are applied to the new psicrystal.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Kalashtar, Arcane Background (Psionics), Smarts d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173257,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"lrB9W23ni6SFqi3K","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Steady Hands","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.OKtVQb5CO4KvNrKj"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Firing from the back of a horse or moving vehicle is tricky business, but your adventurer has figured it out. She ignores the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Unstable Platform]{Unstable Platform}</span><strong> </strong>penalty.</p>\n<p>This also helps when running, reducing the usual penalty from &ndash;2 to &ndash;1 (see @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#movement]{Movement}</span>)</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172483,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"m99Fm8OoSbEZsk6f","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
