{"name":"Improved Double Shot","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[{"_id":"zlQg0Cnkg8cDuOsp","changes":[{"key":"system.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Block","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.HBNdlqoSuo47ToyJ"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The attacker may use her Double Shot Edge twice per turn.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Double Shot, Shooting or Athletics d10+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172320,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"oPPJ7NnsQzQ941Ix","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Warband","type":"edge","img":"icons/sundries/flags/banner-symbol-axe-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fsvlz5d67ma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.C6LLdePT8MWJFhhd"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Legendary leaders attract dedicated fighters to their side. Each time this Edge is taken, five of the champion&rsquo;s @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.OUgrV2GVYekIlhqf]{Followers} gain the @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.UA76PiL4485vout2]{Resilient} Monstrous Ability.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Legendary Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary, Command and at least two other Leadership Edges, Followers"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172853,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"oQ7nQyyaOpfQdlTZ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Coordinated Firepower","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_u9f0tp9vn2","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero knows how to coordinate missile fire against a single foe.</p>\n<p>Instead of firing separately, all missile troops within the hero's command radius yet to act in the round can fire as a single unit on the hero's action (this counts as their entire action for the round).</p>\n<p>The hero nominates one foe within range of his weapon. He then makes a single @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} roll, as appropriate for his weapon. Each additional missile soldier within the hero's command range (and within range of the target), firing at the same time adds a flat +2 to the attack roll.</p>\n<p>Damage is calculated as normal for the hero's weapon, but he adds +1d6 per raise (not just for the first raise). Coordinating fire in this manner counts as a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{single action}.</p>\n<p>A hero cannot use Double Shot or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Giant Killer]{Giant Killer} in conjunction with this Edge unless all subordinates firing with the hero have those Edges as well.</p>\n<p>Although the soldiers lose their individual attacks, the combined firepower gives a better chance of bringing down a large foe (like a dragon), and unlike separate missile fire, the entire damage roll is applied once against the foe's @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Making Characters]{Toughness}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Leadership Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Smarts d6+, Command, Athletics or Shooting d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Hellfrost"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172738,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"oQnUR5ZFmOdGcuTz","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"_id":"oYqv36xqDQmpFJVh","name":"Common Bond","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tbo7kidroy","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.8o2F1b4DT8onc9Xt"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\"><p>Selfless heroes and determined leaders know their greatest strength often comes from their companions, and are willing to give some of their own fortune, fate, or luck to support them.<br />A character with this Edge may freely give her @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.NUjlHH5PBpH1dlzH#bennies]{Bennies} to any other character she can communicate with. The player should explan what form this takes, from a quick shout of encouragement to a welcome pat on the back</span> </p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Social Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Spirit d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173150,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Great Power","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/fire/elemental-fire-humanoid.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lfv57yk1te","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Arcane Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The sorcerer may spend a Benny to cast any single power from thier list of available powers of up to 20 Power Points at a &ndash;2 penalty to his @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.SLOGZKFBCI8VAme7]{Spellcasting} roll. Leftover points are not saved. If the power fails, the sorcerer permanently loses a die type in any one attribute of his choice.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Arcane Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Arcane Background (Sorcerer)"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703171814,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"olo05rxG7sk33Bpt","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Steal Away","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero uses distraction and cover to slip away from his foes.</p>\n<p>The character may make a single @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} roll as a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Actions]{free action} to avoid attack when @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{Withdrawing} from close combat. He suffers a &ndash;1 penalty for each adjacent foe. Failure means foes may attack as normal as the adventurer withdraws.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Stealth d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172486,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"osEBGJYMXkv3JH8e","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Harder To Kill","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.r7ouUc30V4Y9Zb2F"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your hero is tougher to kill than Rasputin. If he is ever &ldquo;killed,&rdquo; roll a die. On an odd result, he's dead as usual. On an even roll, he's @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated} but somehow escapes death. He may be captured, stripped of all his belongings, or mistakenly left for dead, but he somehow survives.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Hard To Kill"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172300,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ouNQSGo9hNX3kYVd","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Expert","type":"edge","img":"icons/sundries/flags/banner-symbol-axe-red.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_fsvlz5d67ma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.C6LLdePT8MWJFhhd"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Professional]{Professional} Edge, increasing the @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Trait} and its limit one additional step.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Legendary Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Professional in affected Trait"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172816,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"pieJx014vAiivrM9","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mark of Warding","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast one of the following spells:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{conceal arcana}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{lock/unlock}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Ward]{ward}</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The heir has 10 dedicated Power Points that recharge normally. She automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} for an additional Power Point. She may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Kundarak]{Mark of Warding} doesn't grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the heir also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or Power Points can be used with the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Kundarak]{Mark of Warding} (and vice-versa).</p>\n<p>Additionally, pick any one of the following skills: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Notice]{Notice}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}, and add +1 to the total whenever they are used.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Dwarf"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172653,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"pkssKFwoQ6Y3ZwE0","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Epic Mastery","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The spellcaster is so well-versed in her arcane or divine craft that she has learned new ways to manipulate her powers. She gains access to the Epic Power Modifiers for all her powers.</p>\n<p>Epic Mastery applies to all a character&rsquo;s Arcane Backgrounds if she has more than one, though she must meet the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1 Powers]{arcane skill} requirement for each before she can use Epic Modifiers with that background&rsquo;s powers.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Arcane Background (Any), arcane skill d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172901,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"prX4uJXK347rENZ6","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"First Strike","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.4ue5lRCW1toPyzWO"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Once per round, as long as he's not @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.OPSttc2CAS2LC1ju.JournalEntryPage.37hOhcNkT98KKtAv]{Stunned},</span> the hero gets a free @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack against a foe immediately after he moves into @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Reach]{Reach}. (See</span><strong> @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Attacks]{Free Attacks}</span></strong>)</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172269,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"qHdt9jw3MRc2kyoS","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Champion","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ueibkknhw27","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.pajf2NwAkxt7TCbY"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Champions are holy (or unholy) men and women chosen to fight for a particular deity or religion. Most are pious souls ready and willing to lay down their lives for a greater cause, but some may have been born into the role and follow their path with some reluctance.</p>\n<p>Champions fight the forces of darkness (or good), adding +2 damage when attacking supernaturally evil (or good if they're evil) creatures. The bonus applies to @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.OPSttc2CAS2LC1ju.JournalEntryPage.CvRlxgap3bhXhnqA]{area effect damage}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Attacks]{ranged attacks}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Powers]{powers}, etc.</p>\n<p>The DM must decide which foes this bonus applies to, but generally it's any evil (or good!) creature born of magic or with any supernatural abilities.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Weird Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Fighting d6+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173318,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"qU47osfy2FOcTAq1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Missile Deflection","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[{"_id":"zlQg0Cnkg8cDuOsp","changes":[{"key":"system.stats.parry.value","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Block","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.HBNdlqoSuo47ToyJ"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero&rsquo;s ability with a melee weapon is unparalleled. As long as he has a melee weapon in hand (or the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.ykb13HKykN48n4m7]{Martial Artist} Edge), physical ranged attacks (arrows, axes, powers with physical @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.URSgjRYJvOeHkDtt]{2 Trappings}, etc.) directed against him (and assuming he can see it coming) use his @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.idEEdHIeNSogKRGm]{Parry} as the base TN.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Fighting d10+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172433,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"qX3Rv4nzuo7Jawxg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Iron Jaw","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.aZ6ywmzKbExqvXuy"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The hero can shrug off even extreme blows. He adds +2 to @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.1hmxcp48L0ZxhzeE.JournalEntryPage.5QA7pQEuHMHqFdoe#soak-rolls]{Soak rolls} and @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Vigor} rolls to avoid <strong>@UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.OPSttc2CAS2LC1ju.JournalEntryPage.l1rEt2RnvcIiEGtQ]{Knockout Blows}</strong></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172389,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"rMqIMujWDnBbbwfO","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"_id":"rZzQkpUfOtIq0Bc6","name":"Favored","type":"edge","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/bust-carved-stone.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kouunmqxeo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Glory Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p><strong>Times may be taken: </strong>2</p>\n<p>The adage that there are old heroes and bold heroes, but no old, bold heroes doesn't apply to this character.</p>\n<p>Whether because he believes in his own legend and refuses to get up when the going gets tough, or whether the gods are smiling on him, the hero can do things other heroes can't.</p>\n<p>He gains a free benny. This adds to his regular total, thus increasing the number he starts each session with.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Glory Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"60+ Glory"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172674,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Nerves of Steel","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[{"_id":"hDKlOijtAKA82b6F","changes":[{"key":"system.wounds.ignored","mode":2,"value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","label":"Nerves of Steel","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null,"origin":null}],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.T3qUSJyJhX4ldoMs"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Your hero has learned to fight on through the most intense pain. He may ignore 1 point of @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d8+"},"grants":[],"source":""},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172435,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ra7xNSRHVaUPHmBr","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Sucker Punch","type":"edge","img":"icons/environment/people/charge.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wbd74crjrma","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>The character doesn't know the meaning of the words \"fair fight.\" If he succeeds in a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test} against an adjacent opponent, the character receives a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Free Attacks]{free attack}. This attack does not incur a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Multi-Actions]{multi-action penalty}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Combat Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, First Strike, Agility d6+, Fighting d8+"},"grants":[],"source":"Slipstream"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172497,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"rhjHrcCkkBF0KbbP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Battle Magic","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-silhouette.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ce260dx4lpo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Z5thwi3zWWr2HXC1"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>This Edge allows the user to cast her spells on large units of Extras such as soldiers, henchmen, or guards. See Battle Magic.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Power Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Arcane Background (Any), arcane skill d10+"},"grants":[],"source":"Fantasy Companion"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172882,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"rlpqDNLmbCwk0aO1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"name":"Mark of Healing","type":"edge","img":"icons/magic/symbols/circled-gem-pink.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_gpnez7cqj7","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Dragonmarked Edges","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast one of the following powers:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em> (<em>@UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Spirit}, @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.F3QL0OVOOYJiYIoO.JournalEntryPage.VWEUOsd2rvNu6ch9]{Vigor}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Science]{Science},</em> and <em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival}</em>)</li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em></li>\n<li><em>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{relief}</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>All powers have the range of touch only, but the heir gains no benefit from the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Limitations]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The heir has 10 dedicated Power Points that recharge normally. She automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Raises]{raise} for 2 additional Power Points. She may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Jorasco]{Mark of Healing} doesn't grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the heir also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or Power Points can be used with the @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Jorasco]{Mark of Healing} (and vice-versa).</p>\n<p>Additionally, pick any one of the following skills: @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Healing]{Healing}, @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Science]{Science}, or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Survival]{Survival}, and add +1 to the total whenever they are used.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Dragonmarked Edges","isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Halfling"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703172621,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"_id":"ryigFO0WRKMhSmxj","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
{"_id":"sZoQ3aU7YydxRNFX","name":"Provoke","type":"edge","img":"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp","effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tbo7kidroy","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.hblegBCavI2AaBJu"},"journal-links":{}},"system":{"description":"<div class=\"sweb-core\">\n<p>Clever characters can manipulate their foes, drawing enemy focus on themselves to protect their allies. Once per turn, when your hero uses @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} for a @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Test]{Test} and gets a raise, she may @Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Provoke]{Provoke} the foe.</p>\n<p>In addition to all the usual effects of the success and raise, the enemy suffers a &ndash;2 penalty to affect any other target besides the one who provoked her. This stacks with @UUID[Compendium.sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-rules.OPSttc2CAS2LC1ju.JournalEntryPage.vsS5QN7dPw9CFsBo]{Distracted} but not further instances of Provoke.</p>\n<p>Provoke lasts until a Joker is drawn, someone else Provokes the target, or the encounter ends. Provoke can affect multiple targets, and may be combined with <strong>@Compendium[sweb-core-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rabble-Rouser]{Rabble-Rouser}</strong>.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"category":"Social Edges","isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Intimidation or Persuasion d6+"},"grants":[],"source":"Savage Eberron"},"_stats":{"systemId":"swade","systemVersion":"2.2.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1675703173171,"lastModifiedBy":"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"7YwiyXiAhNBZZlLf":3}}
